title: divinity fudge
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and water until sugar is dissolved in saucepan.
Cook without stirring to 260 degrees on a candy thermometer.

title: lunchbox cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl combine margarine and shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Stir in flour and baking soda.
Stir in cereal; mix well.
Drop by level tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute vegetables.
Add milk and clams.
Cook.
Add some sour cream before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and the soup together.
Add drained shrimp, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Pour 1/2 of shrimp mixture into a buttered casserole dish; sprinkle with 1/2 of the almonds and Cheddar cheese.
Add rest of shrimp mixture and top with remaining almonds and Cheddar cheese.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix, in order listed, well after each ingredient.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch glass casserole, which has been buttered, for 45 to 60 minutes at 350° (until top is browned).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Do not use salt.
Remove skin and bones.
Set aside; save the broth.
Melt margarine and stir into the bread crumbs.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: In
a
large
mixing bowl combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and
shortening
and
beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time; add
flavoring
and
beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into
a greased
and
floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: boy scout meal
directions: You will need 1 large piece of foil.

title: pork chops smothered
directions: Wash pork chops, salt and pepper, and place in baking dish. Cook at 325 to 350 degrees for about an hour or until done.
Pour soup over the pork chops, heat until bubbling (about 15-20 minutes).
In the meantime cook rice according to package directions.
Make some cornbread and cook a pot of green beans. And you have a good family pleasing meal.

title: angel bars
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together with the coconut.
Add the lemon pie filling.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
If desired, you can add pecan meats.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with a thin powdered sugar frosting.

title: favorite bread stuffing
directions: Over medium heat, melt butter in deep skillet, Dutch oven or casserole.
Add onion, cook to soften, 5 minutes.
Add nuts, stir constant to brown (not burn), 3 minutes.
Add crumbs, tarragon or sage, toss to mix.
Turn heat to low, add salt, pepper and scallions.
Toss again, taste.
Adjust seasoning.
Add parsley, stir, turn off heat.
(Could refrigerate at this point, for a day.) This is enough for a 12 lb. bird.
Pack into turk key, or put in oven-proof casserole.
Bake last 45 minutes along with the turkey.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until golden but not brown.
Add water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add salt and vegetables, except potatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, soup and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add clams and juice.
Cook 10 minutes.
If desired, thicken with flour and water paste.

title: hurry-up turkey roll-ups
directions: In a small bowl, stir together cream cheese, horseradish and mustard.
Generously spread each turkey slice with cream cheese mixture.
Roll up.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Makes 32 to 40 appetizers.

title: browned rice
directions: Saute
onions
in butter.
Add rice and very slowly let it brown,
stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 325°, uncovered.

title: celery seed dressing with lemon
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Add oil gradually, beating constantly with mixer.
Beat until thick.
Yield: makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Mix cheese and oleo; stir in other ingredients until blended. Chill. Shape into 1-inch balls. Cook on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sotte suppe(norwegian sweet soup)
directions: Boil until tender and add tapioca on low heat.
Stir often. Serve warm with cream poured on (diluted with milk if you wish). Or serve cold with whipped cream.

title: golabki(polish stuffed cabbage rolls)
directions: Saute onions and meat until brown.
Mix meat with rice and 1 can tomato soup. Trim outer leaves from cabbage and discard. Core cabbage and immerse remainder of cabbage head in boiling salted water.
Parboil cabbage until leaves are pliable. Drain thoroughly.
Place meat mix on each cabbage leaf.
Fold in ends, then roll (envelope fashion).
Line bottom of roaster with cabbage leaves.
Place layer of cabbage rolls in roaster.
Cover each layer with 1/2 can soup and 1/2 can water, mixed.
Salt and pepper. Repeat layers. Top with cabbage leaves. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Add tomato/water mix as necessary.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well after each addition. Batter will be thick and heavy.
Pour in greased oblong casserole dish or sheet cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot grease, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: egg noodles
directions: In a medium bowl, beat lightly eggs, salt and food coloring. Add flour, 1/4 cup at a time, until blended.
Then knead dough until it is stiff.
Roll on lightly floured surface into a thin circle and cut into quarters.
Slice into strips the width you like.
Spread noodles on a cloth and dry overnight.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water. Add undrained pineapple and lemon juice. Chill until very thick. Fold in carrots and nuts.

title: paella(spain)
directions: Fry the chicken and set aside.
Fry garlic in remaining oil until brown.
Add onion, then bacon cubes and fried chicken.
Add tomato puree, paprika, sweet pepper and the water in which clams were cooked.
Add rice and allow to simmer until mixture is almost dry and the rice cooked.
Add the prawns, crabs, clams and peas and cover well.
Continue cooking over low heat until all the water has dried up.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken breasts and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of this and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with dried parsley flakes and serve with rice or noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and heat until warm.
Crush chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 chicken mix on top of chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Layer again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine Graham Cracker Crumbs and 1 stick of melted Margarine. Place in bottom of Tupperware cold cut container or similar casserole dish.
Beat in a bowl Sugar, Eggs and 2 sticks Margarine for 15 minutes.
Layer this mixture on top of Graham Cracker Crumb in dish.
Then add sliced Bananas, then add Crushed Pineapple and top with the Cool Whip.

title: bruce's easy chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken about 30 to 45 minutes or until it is falling apart.
Drain and cool.
Save 3 cups of chicken broth.
Pick chicken off bone and put chicken back in broth.
Combine all ingredients.

title: pork tenderloin diane
directions: Cut tenderloin into 8 crosswise pieces.
Press each slice into 1-inch thickness. Sprinkle surfaces of medallions with lemon-pepper.
Heat butter in heavy skillet, cook medallions 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove to a serving platter, keep warm. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to skillet. Cook, stirring with pan juices, until heated through.
Pour sauce over medallions, sprinkle with parsley or chives and serve.

title: strawberry roll
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn out on towel which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up towel and let cool.
When cooled, unroll and sprinkle sliced strawberries over cake.
Spread whipped cream on top of berries and roll back up.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter in 425° oven.
In separate bowl, beat eggs at high speed; gradually add milk, then flour and pour in pan.
Bake until puffy and well browned, about 20 or 25 minutes.
Dust with nutmeg and powdered sugar.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Boil
potatoes
with
skins
on
until
about 2/3 done. Cool. Peel
and
coarsely grate.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or pan.
Mix together the next 4 ingredients and 1/4 cup of
the margarine.
Fold
this mixture into the potatoes. Mix the
corn flakes
with the remaining 1/4 cup of margarine and spread on
top of the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: easy sherbet
directions: Electric or hand-turned ice cream freezer
method:
Pour sweetened condensed milk and beverage into ice cream freezer container.
Proceed according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: cheesy chicken fajitas
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam cooking spray.
Add pepper strips and onion.
Cook and stir until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Spray skillet with Pam again.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir until cooked through.
Add cooked vegetables, chilies, cumin and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place each tortilla on microwaveable plate.
Top with 2 Kraft Free singles.
Microwave on High for 20 seconds.
Top each tortilla with half of chicken mixture.
Fold sides to middle.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 2 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and pour oleo over all.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: frozen yogurt salad
directions: Beat whipping cream at medium speed with a mixer until soft peaks form.
Gradually add honey, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in yogurt and fruit.
Spoon into 10 lightly oiled 1/2-molds. Cover and freeze at least 8 hours.

title: company hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion; drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Re-cover for 5 minutes.

title: mother's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press flat with tines of fork.
Leave plain or decorate with sugar or chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 9 dozen small cookies.

title: june's beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Slice onion and place in the bottom of a Dutch oven or heavy pan.
Wipe beef brisket with a damp cloth and season with pepper and paprika to taste.
Place beef in pan on top of onions.
Bake in open pan for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and decrease heat to 325°.
Pour can of Coke over beef and seal pan with heavy aluminum foil.
Return to oven.
Cook for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove beef from pan.
Wrap in foil to let cool.
Pour juice from pan into bowl and place in refrigerator.
When cool and fat has formed on top, remove fat and reserve
juice for serving with meat.
When ready to serve, trim fat from meat and slice across the grain. A sauce of mayo and horseradish to taste may be served on the side.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Chop bacon; put in pan with butter.
Cook gently a few minutes.
Add celery, potato and onion; cook together 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly, to prevent browning.
Sprinkle in flour; blend smoothly.
Add stock; mix well.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Add bay leaf, parsley and thyme; simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Put through fine food mill or into electric blender or food processor; blend until smooth. Reheat gently.

title: cucumber cuties(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Peel cucumber.
Remove seeds in center with apple core remover.
Mix cream cheese, chives, parsley, mustard and mayonnaise to soften.
Stuff the cucumber.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.

title: harvard beets
directions: Blend sugar, salt and cornstarch in double boiler; stir in vinegar, then cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly. Add butter, onion and beets, and heat 20 minutes longer.
Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, raisins, Bac*Os (or bacon) and onion (if desired).
In a separate bowl, mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and then toss with broccoli.

title: oven fried chicken and rice
directions: Pour
into
a 13 x 9-inch buttered
pan
rice,
chicken soup, onion soup and water.
Mix together.
Lay cut up chicken on top and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: asparagus lasagna
directions: Cook onions and mushrooms in melted butter until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring until thickened, about 8 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Combine onion, celery and chopped eggs; sprinkle over chicken.
Combine soup and broth; pour over chicken. Combine baking mix and milk; pour evenly over other ingredients. Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain and put in crock-pot.
Add refried beans, salsa and chili mix; mix well.
Let simmer all day.
Put in a pan; grate cheese on top.
Serve with chips or nachos.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Saute vegetables in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add soy sauce until brown.
Mix rice, shrimp and eggs with vegetables.
Serves 6.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix according to package directions.
Add pudding mix, sour cream and vanilla extract.
Toss chocolate chips (and nuts) with 2 tablespoons of cocoa powder.
Add to first mixture.
Grease cake pan with Crisco and cocoa powder.
Pour mix into pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour or until a toothpick in center of cake comes out clean.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake on pancake griddle.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt; then refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: microwave peanut brittle(makes about 1 pound)
directions: Butter a large baking sheet or cookie sheet.
In microwave-proof bowl (allow room for expansion), combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High until mixture bubbles vigorously, about 6 minutes (cooking time may
vary slightly due to the differences in microwave power).
Remove mixture from microwave and stir in butter and vanilla.
Return to microwave and cook on High until candy turns light gold color (about 3 minutes).
Remove bowl from microwave (carefully, it's hot!).
Working quickly, add baking soda to mixture and stir briskly.
The mixture will foam up.
Immediately pour onto buttered baking sheet and shake from side to side to spread brittle as thin as possible.
Let stand until cold and hard (about 45 minutes).
Break into pieces and store in airtight container at room temperature for up to a month.

title: barbecued wieners for a crowd
directions: Cut wieners in about
1 1/2 inch pieces.
Put in crock-pot with grape jelly
and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 4 or 5 hours in crock-pot.	 Serve	 with	favorite
crackers.
Good
for parties.

title: french fried sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse sweet potatoes and peel.
Cut into 3/4-inch strips.
Dry potatoes on paper towel.
Fry in deep oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: champagne punch
directions: Chill punch bowl.
Mix sugar and Curacao thoroughly in pitcher.
Stir in cognac and cherry juice.
Pour into bowl. Place sherbet in center of bowl.
Slowly add champagne, then fruit slices.
Do not stir after champagne is added.
Yields 25 punch cups.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix (follow steps on back).
Add refried beans to taco meat.
Heat all together.
Pour dip into baking dish and top with shredded cheese. Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: starlight mint cookies(mrs. alfred j. orlidge)
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs, water and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Open a package of Rockwood chocolate mint wafers.
Enclose each wafer in 1 tablespoon of dough.
Place pecan on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carol's favorite fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together in microwave for 1 minute.
Add eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Slice and enjoy with cold milk.

title: jim dandy cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° until a golden brown.
Combine evaporated milk, sugar and margarine and cook over low heat until butter melts; pour baked cake.
Mix together pecans and coconut; sprinkle over top of cake.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, milk and egg.
Shape into twenty meatballs.
Brown well in two tablespoons oil.
Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle meatballs with flour and stir gently to coat.
Cut tomatoes into bite-size pieces.
Combine tomatoes and their liquid with Heinz 57 sauce and salt.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: curried rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo in ovenproof dish.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is translucent.
Add the rice and stir to coat all the grains with butter.
Sprinkle with curry powder and coriander; stir to blend.
Stir in broth.
Cover with close-fitting lid and bake exactly 17 minutes.
Add remaining oleo.

title: sugar spiced nuts
directions: In a 1-quart glass dish, combine brown sugar, salt, spices and water.
Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes, stirring once.
Add 1/2 cup nuts to syrup mix.
Stir with fork until coated, then lift out nuts with fork to drain excess syrup and place in single layer in oblong glass dish.
Cook, uncovered, 4 minutes or until syrup on nuts begins to harden slightly.
Transfer nuts to waxed paper to cool until crisp.
Will keep 6 to 8 weeks.
Wonderful!

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mandarin chicken breast
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast generously with pepper and chicken soup mix.
Coat a large skillet with oil.
Place skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken to skillet and cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
(steam)
squash
and
drain.
Add
carrot, onion, pimento,
soup,
sour
cream,
salt and pepper to taste.
Melt margarine, add dressing and line bottom of casserole dish with half
of dressing.	Pour squash mixture over this and top with remainder of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried potatoes and onion
directions: Fry on medium-high heat and serve.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix ingredients. Serve over fresh greens.

title: low-fat king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Crush Tostitos and spread in bottom of dish.
Add diced chicken.
Blend remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly for about 40 minutes.
Serves 12. There are 3.5 grams of fat per serving, 150 calories per serving.

title: mary k. salad
directions: Mix together and put in freezer.
Can be used as a salad or pie filling with graham cracker crust.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until brown.
Drain and spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir in taco mix and tomato sauce. Pour in corn and sprinkle with cheese. Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour over beef mixture. Bake for 35 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce in desired amounts. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients and put into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: jennifer's macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Cook macaroni and drain. In 3-quart saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour. Cook over medium heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Stir in the milk, cream cheese, salt, pepper and mustard; continue cooking until it thickens. Stir in the macaroni and cubed cheese. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. In small bowl, stir melted butter and bread crumbs together. Sprinkle on top of macaroni. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 2 inch deep casserole.
Place all ingredients in order.
Do not mix.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Line an 11 x 7-inch baking pan with foil, letting ends extend above pan on 2 sides.
Lightly grease foil.
Heat chocolate chips, butter and corn syrup in a medium size saucepan over low heat, stirring once or twice, until chocolate and butter are melted. Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of the cinnamon, marshmallows and cereal until blended.
Scrape mixture from saucepan into prepared pan and press firmly with spatula into an even layer.
Mix remaining cinnamon with the sugar.
Sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Lift foil by ends onto cutting board.
Cut in bars and store at room temperature.

title: toasted cheese
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients together; add mayonnaise to make a paste.
Spread on bread.
Put sliced pimento olives on top and broil.

title: skillet fish italiano
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in butter until tender; add fish, lemon juice, oregano, zucchini and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese; cover and simmer 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: kathryn's spice cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and applesauce.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Mix and bake in loaf pan in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
One-half cup of nuts and 1/2 cup raisins may be chopped, floured and added.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook all day.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine the sugars, milk and margarine in a medium-sized pan. Bring to a boil.
Boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Pour over popcorn and stir.

title: pecan wafers
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper to creamed mixture.
Stir in cereal.
Chill 2 hours.

title: salad creole
directions: Cut everything into small portions.
Mix lemon juice, salt and oil.
Pour mixture over.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick.

title: cole slaw
directions: Toss together cabbage, sugar and salt.	Let
stand 5 to 10 minutes to allow cabbage to bleed.	Don't
drain off juice. While cabbage
is bleeding, combine mayonnaise
and
vinegar. Mix
well. Fold
this thoroughly into
cabbage.
Refrigerate until needed. Serves 4 to 5.
You may add a
small
amount of onion to this if desired.

title: hummus
directions: Put all ingredients, except chickpeas, in a blender and blend them together. Add chickpeas a few at a time and blend until smooth.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown 1 pound hamburger (crumbled); drain. Mix all ingredients together in large baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Layer sausage in long, greased glass casserole.
Sprinkle bread cubes, then cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, sage, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce together and pour over sausage, bread and cheese.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before baking at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook the chicken in 3 quarts water.
When done, remove chicken; add noodles.
When done, drain and add vegetables and soup.
Stir until the soup is liquified.
Skin and chop chicken, add to noodles.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender; do not drain.
Add cream, corn, peas and salmon; add margarine and mix thoroughly. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer 1 hour.
Serve with crackers on cold day.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together yellow cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add 1 egg beaten lightly, butter and enough milk to make a soft dough.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In greased casserole dish layer thinly sliced onions, tomatoes and squash.
Add a few bread crumbs (fresh bread) or cracker crumbs.
Use Italian seasoning and grated cheese.
Repeat layers to suit the needs of your family.
End with cracker layer.
A meat layer may be added if you like (hamburg, pork or sausage).

title: ambrosia fruit salad for 12
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: old fashioned stuffing
directions: Fry onion and ground beef until cooked.
Boil giblets until tender and chop.
Mix all of ingredients together.
Stuff turkey.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; cut in shortening until mix is crumbly.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in water; add buttermilk and knead for several minutes.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 450° until golden brown (approximately 12 minutes).
May keep dough in sealed container in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: cajun shrimp and pasta
directions: Saute (except shrimp) ingredients up to parsley until onions are tender.

Add 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 1/4 to 2 tablespoons cayenne pepper, almost 1/4 cup sherry, 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons chili powder, 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce, 1/3 cup ham, and 1/4 pound mushrooms.
Saute 1 hour. (You can freeze sauce now.)
Add shrimp saute.
Serve over 1/3 (16 ounce) box fettuccini or rice.

title: tarragon dressing(prepare the day before)
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
There it is! Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave coffeecake bread
directions: Put 1 tablespoon butter in small bowl.
Microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir in cracker crumbs; set aside.
Put 1/2 cup butter in medium mixing bowl.
Microwave 15 to 30 seconds.
Add flour, brown sugar and egg.
Cream at high speed with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients; whip.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This recipe serves a good crowd.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine together.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Mix.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well.
Press in bottom of dish.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Cool and add nuts and marshmallows; mix well.
Sprinkle coconut on 3 pieces wax paper. Spoon mixture on paper and roll into log form.
Put log on foil and roll and seal.
Put in refrigerator overnight, then slice and put on platter.

title: salmon balls(deep fried)
directions: Pour salmon juice into measuring cup and set aside.
Put salmon in bowl and add egg.
Mix with fork.
When gummy, add flour.
Stir with fork.
Do not add salt.
To 1/4 cup of salmon juice, add baking powder.
Beat with fork.
Pour into the salmon. Add onion, parsley flakes and pepper when adding juice to salmon. Fry in small balls in deep fat.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix
thoroughly the shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in the buttermilk
and
vanilla.
Sift
together
and stir in the flour, baking
soda,
salt
and cocoa.
Chill at least 1 hour. Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to
10 minutes.
When cool, frost with your favorite creamy frosting. Makes 3 dozen.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water according to directions. Drain.
Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Add onions and green pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add noodles and tuna.
Place in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender; drain.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix
ingredients
until
thoroughly
combined.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap;	let stand 3 to 5 days, stir once a day.
Refrigerate
after
days
in
covered
container
for freshness.	Will keep
for	2 weeks.
Be sure to stir daily or expanding starter may break the covered container.	Use in any standard sourdough recipe.

title: fruit cocktail pudding(tastes like date torte)
directions: Sift flour once; measure and sift into bowl with soda, salt and sugar.
Beat egg and add cocktail, juice and all, and vanilla. Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Put in 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Sprinkle top of batter with 1 cup light brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Bake in 300° oven about 40 minutes or until center stops bubbling.
Cut into squares when cool (9 pieces). Serve with whipped cream.

title: creamy peach dessert
directions: Drain juice from peaches and mix with pudding.
Cut up peaches to bite size and add to pudding.
Add 1 or 2 cups of mini marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Can be made in advance.

title: fried cabbages
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, carrot and green pepper together.
Add salt, peppers and sugar.
Fry in hot grease until done.
Serve while hot.

title: be'arnaise sauce (france)
directions: Here we are preparing a reduced Bearnaise Sauce that is stirred into Hollandaise Sauce.
Can be prepared days ahead and refrigerated.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, and beat well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add all with flour and beat well.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Fold into well beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in tube pan, 30 to 35 minutes in 8-inch pan or bake in 2 (9-inch) greased pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown cubed meat slowly in oil.
Add onions and garlic. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer uncovered for 3 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
May be frozen with excellent results.
Serve with heated tortillas.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir first 4 ingredients.
Cook 8 minutes in microwave on High.
Stir well after 4 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; cook 1 minute on High.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Spread thinly.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: cucumbers bowl
directions: Mix; cover 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in blueberry pie filling and drained pineapple.
Chill until firmly set, then blend together sour cream, cream cheese, whipped cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon on top of Jell-O mixture.
Top with pecans.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Pour cake into greased mini-muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt butter.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Remove muffins from pan while still warm, brush with butter and dip in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: black bean burritos(serves 5)
directions: In a heated skillet, soften a tortilla by heating it for about 20 seconds.
Spread a generous 1/4 cup of beans across the middle of the tortilla.
Top with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese.
Wrap the tortilla around the filling and place the burrito, seam side down, in a greased baking dish.
Spread salsa on top of burritos and top with remaining cheese.
bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, salsa and sour cream.

title: dodie's dills
directions: Bring barely to a boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pack cucumbers in jar.
Put 1 grape leaf, 2 cloves garlic and 1 sprig of fresh dill in the bottom of jar.
Pour liquid mixture over pickles.
Add 4 peppercorns to each jar.
Put through hot water bath 10 minutes. Use small cucumbers 2 1/2 to 3-inches long.
These are crispier. Add another sprig of dill and another grape leaf on top.
Use all fresh ingredients.

title: jello delight
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream the cream cheese and drained pineapple together, then beat in the Cool Whip.
After dissolving jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water, add about 8 ice cubes to cool jello, then add to rest of the mixture.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch Tupperware with lid or same size oblong glass dish with lid.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Best made the night before for next day.
Can be a salad or dessert.

title: raisin bran cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine or butter.
Add the brown sugar and sugar; cream well.
Combine the egg, vanilla and milk.
Beat into mixture.
Sift the baking soda, baking powder, salt and sifted flour together.
Add dry ingredients to the mixture.
When beaten smooth, add the Raisin Bran.
Beat the mixture well.
Drop cookies 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain fruit; save juice for later use. In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mushroom salad garay
directions: Turn mushrooms into a deep glass bowl.
Combine oil, wine vinegar, Beau Monde, salad herbs, nutmeg and pepper in a small saucepan.
Bring mixture just to a boil.

title: brown sugar square cookies
directions: Stir together (do not beat) the egg, brown sugar and vanilla. Quickly stir in flour, soda and salt. Blend in walnuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
You may have to wet fingers and press dough to fit entire pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or longer. Top should be lightly browned, but soft in center when taken from oven. Cool in pan, then cut into squares.

title: breadsticks
directions: Combine the yeast, sugar, ginger and water in a large bowl. Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix in the oil and salt, then slowly mix in the flour, adding just enough to get past the sticky stage and allow you to knead the dough.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Roll into long sticks, about 1/2-inch thick x 8-inches long.
Place the sticks on a lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 375° on the high rack of the oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yield:
2 dozen sticks.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Spread cooked rice in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soups with 1/2 cup water.
Spread 1/2 on top of rice.
Put raw chicken on top of soup.
Dot with butter; season to taste, then add rest of soup and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.

title: salsa(makes 3 quarts)
directions: In a food processor, puree one can of tomatoes at a time and pour into large bowl.
Cut onion half into quarters and process to a fine chop; add to bowl.
Wearing plastic gloves, cut pepper ends off; remove insides and cut in half.
Process to fine chop; add to bowl.
Add vinegar and salt to bowl and mix well.
Chop tomatoes by hand to coarse texture and add to bowl.
Mix well and chill. Serve with tortilla chips.
Sometimes after chilling, it thickens too much for dipping.
Thin with more vinegar.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth. Stir in onion and parsley. Chill for at least 1 hour before serving to blend flavors.

title: portuguese sweet rice pudding
directions: Add milk, sugar, butter and salt in large pan and bring to a boil.
Add rice and reduce heat to low.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Beat eggs.
Add these slowly to the mixture.
Keep stirring and cook for a few more minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Garnish with cinnamon.

title: chip beef christmas dip(or anytime)
directions: Rinse onions and pat them dry with paper towel. Chop into small pieces. Combine other ingredients and mix well. May be served right away or refrigerated several hours.

title: lemon salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple in saucepan.
Stir in Jell-O and heat.
Put in marshmallows.
Let come to a boil.
Stir well. Cool.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add mashed bananas, applesauce and milk.
Beat on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs or egg substitute and remaining 3/4 cup flour. Beat until blended. Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: jello salad
directions: You will need 1 roll of paper towels.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip in milk; dust with flour and brown in butter.
Cook very slow.
Transfer to a baking dish.
Add onion to butter in skillet and cook until clear but not brown.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and water to make gravy.
Use rest of milk.
Add mushrooms and sherry.
Pour over browned chicken and cool overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Baste and turn while baking.

title: north china hot and sour beef
directions: Cut meat across the grain in 1-inch strips.
Marinate meat in soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of white wine, cornstarch and sugar for 30 minutes at
room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.

title: olivia's steam pot
directions: Place red potatoes in a large 16 to 18-quart stockpot.
Cover with water and boil 15 minutes. Add sausage. Sprinkle corn with seasoning mix and add to pot. Boil 10 minutes.
Add crab legs. Cover pot and steam 5 minutes. Sprinkle shrimp with seasoning mix. Add to pot and steam 3 minutes.
Drain off liquid and pile on a big platter.
Melt butter for crab legs.
Use seafood cocktail sauce for shrimp.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage.
Add salt and pepper; boil for 10 minutes, then drain off water.
Cream butter and flour in small saucepan, then add the hot milk and salt.
Bring to a boil. Butter a small casserole dish; sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Put sauce and cabbage in layers in baking dish.
Cover with crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and brown.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil, without stirring, to 234° (soft boil stage) or until syrup when dropped into very cold water forms soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
Beat until fudge loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread in buttered pan; cool.
Cut into squares or drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine onion, zucchini and salt; let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and line cake pan with wax paper.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut
on bottom.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Spread
in
pan
over
nuts
and coconut.
Next, melt butter
and cream cheese over low heat, stirring continuously until smooth. Next, fold in powdered sugar a little at a time until blended. Pour
mixture evenly over cake mix and bake at 350° for
45 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan and dump it out bottom side up on tray.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except butter and crumbs; mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, serves 20.

title: traveling taco
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: In saucepan, saute first 3 ingredients in butter until soft. Add remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Heat to boiling, simmer, uncovered for 20 minutes to thicken.
Serve with grilled meats or cold meats.
Makes 4 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Bake 1
hour in a 300° oven in greased and floured pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls on 12 x 18-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 12 minutes; cool.
Blend remaining ingredients. Spread evenly on cooled dough.
Cut into approximately 4 inch squares.
Top with vegetables.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, soup, Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper and onion together.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove top and bake 30 minutes more.

title: easy peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until it spins a thread.
Add the peanuts and cook until (scorchy looking) light brown.
Remove from heat and add soda. Stir good.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and spread thin.
Cool.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Over low fire, mix in a saucepan mushroom soup, cream cheese and Knox gelatine.
Cook until cheese melts.
Take off of heat. Mix all ingredients well.
Put into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook the ziti according to directions on box; drain.
Mix Ricotta cheese, spaghetti sauce and cooked ziti together.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: plantation cake
directions: Cream shortening thoroughly.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, lemon and flour; beat.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: ingrid's holiday bowl cake
directions: You will need 1 large, thick glass punch bowl.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Combine one cup milk, 1/2 cup butter, salt and 1/2 cup sugar in a large saucepan until just warm. In a small mixing bowl, combine yeast and water until yeast is dissolved. Add remaining sugar. When yeast mixture begins to foam, add to milk mixture. Mix well. Fold in egg. Add flour and knead just until smooth. Roll dough out on a floured surface to a 16 x 12-inch rectangle. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture to taste. Dot with remaining butter. Roll up dough lengthwise and cut into 1-inch slices. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise 25 minutes or until double. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Combine powdered sugar, remaining milk and vanilla. Drizzle over rolls. Makes 1 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add soda to dates and cover with boiling water.
Let cool. Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, then add date mixture and nuts. Let rise in loaf pan 15 minutes, then bake 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix together potatoes, milk, salt and spices.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add to potato mixture and blend well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Stir twice while baking.

title: jalapeno grits
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Bake in a single pie crust for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: salmon-horseradish spread
directions: Drain and flake salmon after removing skin and discarding bones.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Chill several hours. Serve with crackers.

title: banana oat cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut in oleo with pastry blender.
Add egg, bananas, oats and nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls, about 1 inch apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice as directed; mix with Mexicorn, butter and soup.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk over boiling water in top of double boiler.
Lower heat and add seasonings and butter.
Simmer about 15 minutes; add oysters and cook 15 more minutes.
Pour into bowls and top with a pat of butter and parsley.
Serve with oyster crackers.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper or cookie sheets. Refrigerate to harden.

title: breaded baked pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in beaten egg and milk.
Dip in bread crumbs. Fry in oil until golden brown on both sides.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Cream butter and add other ingredients, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: streusel cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sugar and flour; add the butter. Cut in pieces and rub with your fingers until mixture is reduced to fine crumbs.
Stir in nuts; spoon out and set aside 1 cup of this mixture for topping.
To the remaining crumbs, add the soda and salt.

title: golden orange punch
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, bring to a boil and set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and add sugar and water mixture. Freeze in two 1-gallon zip lock bags.
Remove from freezer approximately two hours before use to thaw. Put in punch bowl and add two bottles of ginger ale per bag.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook until bubbly; cover with cheese.

title: rainbow jello
directions: First Layer:
In bowl, mix 1 package jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water until jello is dissolved.
Cool until lukewarm. Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Refrigerate for 30 to 40 minutes until jello sets.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion over chicken.
Slice cheese over chicken completely.
Place mushrooms over cheese; crumble Doritos over mushrooms.
Blend soups and tomatoes together and pour over chips.
You may want to top this off with a little more cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: birchermuesli
directions: *I always include mashed fresh strawberries or frozen strawberries with their juice to give it a pink color.

title: peach punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add ginger ale last, just before serving.
One may want to freeze some of the punch with pineapple slices, cherries, etc.
Serves 30.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Melt Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel in microwave.
Boil onion until done.
Combine all ingredients except Tostitos.
In casserole dish, put a layer of mixture, layer Tostitos; repeat until all gone.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Combine all ingredients except sauce, adding eggs last.
Mix well.
Heat 2 tablespoons salad oil in skillet and spoon in 1/3 cup egg mixture to form each cake.
Fry over high heat until puffed and delicately browned, turning once.
Stack several cakes for each serving and pass Egg Foo Yong Sauce.
Makes 6 cakes.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Drain orange, saving juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add juice.
Chill until thick.
Fold in rest of ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: mickey's french bread pizza
directions: Cut bread into thirds, then cut each piece in half lengthwise, making 6 pieces.
Spread each piece of French bread with margarine. Top each piece with prepared pizza sauce.
Cover sauce with sliced pepperoni.
Top meat with sliced fresh mushrooms, chopped green pepper and, if desired, sliced black olives (about 2 cups total). Sprinkle lots of Mozzarella cheese over veggies.
Sprinkle Mozzarella with Parmesan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to instructions on box.
When cooled, break into small pieces.
Add rest of ingredients.
Top with additional cheese, if desired.
Chill before serving.

title: cabbage dish
directions: Place cabbage in a greased baking dish.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in rice.
Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage. Cover with tomato soup and water.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pastry shell; place meringue on top.
Delicious.
Serves 6.

title: old talbott tavern corn fritters
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients, using just enough milk to moisten.
Batter should be stiff.
Drop by tablespoon into deep oil at 325° and fry to golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar and serve warm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.
Great with a vegetable platter or watered down as a salad dressing.
Can be made the day before.

title: three cheese spinach rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Cool in large bowl of cold water; set aside. Saute onion and red pepper with 3 tablespoons of butter or margarine, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine spinach, onion, red pepper, 1 1/2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and egg; set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter or margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Add pepper and salt.
Stir in milk, cream and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir until thick.
Remove noodles from water.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Spread about 1/2 cup of spinach mixture over each noodle.
Roll up jelly roll fashion starting at short end.
Spread a small amount of sauce on the bottom of buttered 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Place rolls in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over roll-ups.
Sprinkle with remaining shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 persons.
Add toss salad and garlic bread for a complete meal.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Plumb (cook) raisins in 1 1/4 cups of water; cook slowly about 10 minutes.
There will be some liquid left on the raisins; cool. Melt 4 tablespoons of oleo and cool some.
Add sugar, oleo and applesauce.
Mix soda and spices with flour.
Add flour mixture and raisins a little at a time, mixing well after each addition, including any liquid left on raisins and nuts.
Pour into a Bundt pan that has been greased and floured and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick ham and cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix ham, vegetables and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs with fork until blended.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake for 30 minutes if using Bisquick reduced fat baking mix.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Make up dry and keep for individual cups of tea, hot or cold. Use 2 to 3	teaspoons
per	cup.
(Sugar may be omitted and added to cup per individual taste.)

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Mix Jell-O, almonds and coconut together; stir in milk and flavoring.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries; roll in red sugar.
Insert almond slivers for stems.
Store in tight container in refrigerator.
(Use 1/2 teaspoon of mixture for each strawberry.)
Yield:

title: root beer cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl. Blend at low speed; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except eggs and cheese.
Beat eggs well.
Mix with corn.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Add salt, onions, sour cream and cheese. Mix and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour melted butter over casserole and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning mixture.
Combine 1/2 jar (8 ounces) picante sauce with cream cheese.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with ground beef, then remaining picante sauce. Top with shredded cheese.

title: sweet mexican corn
directions: Drain corn well.
Melt butter in skillet (cast-iron works best).
Add corn, green pepper, red pepper or tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until all liquid has cooked out.
Stir frequently.
Add sweetener and serve.

title: banana wheat germ rolls
directions: This is a nutritious snack that should be completely prepared by the children.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream the butter and add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Refrigerate until well chilled, several days if needed.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Watch carefully to avoid burning.
Let cool for just a few minutes before removing cookies with a spatula to silver foil where they should cool completely before placing in tin container with tight lid (preferably).
Put a little silver foil on top of cookies after they are placed in container to retain crispness.

title: oriental beef casserole
directions: Saute meat in fat.
Add next 7 ingredients, using only 1/2 cup of celery.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add sour cream, remaining celery and spaghetti to meat mixture and mix well.
Put in a 14 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle top with slivered almonds.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ranch stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out center of potatoes; mix it with sour cream and Ranch dressing.
Fill potatoes with mix and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: glazed pork tenderloin
directions: Mix soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and honey.
Pour over tenderloin in 8-inch square pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and marinate overnight.
Turn several times.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the cup of boiling water.
Add cold water to make 1 cup.
Add lemon juice.
Mix together until semi-congealed. To crushed pineapple, add the nuts, celery, cranberry relish and apple.
Pour into a 2-quart dish (oblong).
Chill; cut into squares.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and put in well-greased pan (I use a Bundt or tube pan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool. Take flour and milk (after cooled) and mix with remaining ingredients.
Add food coloring of your choice.

title: ollie bolin -- oma lavooy's recipe
directions: Boil water; add butter, then flour.
When thickened, remove from

title: quick jello mix
directions: Mix the Jell-O "powder" with the Cool Whip and whip with beater.
Add rest of ingredients and chill in a 9 x 9-inch dish.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cocoa alternately with milk.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients (except soup) in order listed.
Mix well.
Form into patties and roll lightly in flour.
Brown on both sides in butter or margarine (1/2 stick).
Pour soup with one can of water over meat patties and simmer in covered pan for 45 minutes.

title: aunt martha's prune cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Sift flour with spices and add with milk.
Add prunes and nuts, then soda dissolved in a little boiling water.
Beat for 1 minute.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: braised venison
directions: Cut venison into 1/2-inch serving size pieces. Dip in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Heat butter in skillet. Brown meat quickly and evenly. Put venison in shallow pan and cover with venison marinade. Cook in slow oven (300°) until tender (about 2 hours). Watch and add water from time to time if necessary.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good for celery, cauliflower, tomatoes, broccoli or any raw vegetable.

title: polish dill pickles
directions: Boil together water, vinegar, sugar and salt; let cool.
Pack a gallon glass jar (or smaller) with cukes.
Add 2 cloves, slice of onion, clove of garlic and 1/2 teaspoon of pickling spice. Place dill on bottom and top of pickles.
Pour cooled vinegar solution over cucumbers and close cover.
Let stand at room temperature, then place in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 24 hours.
Lasts a month.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat egg;
stir in
milk
and
oil. Mix remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: schnitzel(pork)
directions: Pound cutlets with mallet.
Dip in eggs.
Mix bread crumbs together.
Cover dipped cutlets with crumbs.
Dip back into eggs. Cover with crumbs again.
Brown in skillet with 1/2 stick butter and 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Place in pan with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake in oven at 275° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil while baking.
Serve with lemon juice.

title: barbecue roasted salmon
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a zip-lock bag; seal and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Remove fish from bag; discard marinade. Combine sugar and next 5 ingredients (sugar through cinnamon) in a bowl.
Rub over fish; place in a 11 X 7 inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.
Prep time:
1 hour, 10 minutes.
Cooking time:
15 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar together for one or 1 1/2 minutes. Pour on kraut.
Let stand overnight.

title: honeybear brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a small bowl: blend in honey or corn syrup and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, cocoa, and salt, gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 3/4 in. pan, (or double the recipe and use a 13 x 9 in. pan.)
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away form the sides.
Cool.
Frost with your favorite frosting or eat as they are.
Yields: 16 brownies.

title: forever ambers(cookies)
directions: Mix well; spread on cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool enough to handle.
Roll into balls about 1 inch and roll in powdered sugar.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric beater.
Mash and add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Mix until just combined.
Spoon mixture into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: west germany pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Beat in sugar; add flour, soda and pineapple and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake 40 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water in covered saucepan for 10 minutes. Dice into cooking liquid. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Heat to serving temperature. Makes 12 servings.

title: jiffy peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in
a
double
boiler and stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: walnut squares
directions: Stir sugar, egg and vanilla together in bowl (don't beat hard). Sift flour with salt and soda; stir in.
Add nuts.
Spread stiff batter in greased, shallow 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown, but should still be soft.
Leave in pan.
Cut into squares or bars.
I roll them in powdered sugar to prevent them from sticking to each other.

title: cider waldorf salad
directions: Bring 1 cup apple cider or juice to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling cider.
Stir in remaining cider or juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apple, celery, and pecans.
Pour into a 3-cup mold, or spoon into 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm.

title: veal stew
directions: Heat butter and oil.
Saute onions until translucent.
Season veal with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Brown veal on both sides in oil.
Add can of tomatoes and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add peas about 15 minutes before cooking is completed.
Serve over noodles.

title: christmas cheese logs
directions: Grate cheese and garlic.
Cut cream cheese into squares; leave until it reaches room temperature.
Add cream cheese to pimento cheese spread and other grated cheeses.
Mix well together.
Roll into logs or balls.
Place on wax paper; roll in paprika.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 2 large cheese balls or 4 cheese logs.

title: hearty farm special
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add celery and onion and saute several minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, pork and beans and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese on top.
Return to the oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put dried beef in bottom of pan, then put in cooked chicken. Then put 1/2 cup of water and golden mushroom soup over chicken. Cover.
Bake at 400° until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: In
quart casserole. Combine apples, cranberries and granulated	sugar.	Top with mixture of remaining ingredients. Bake in 350°
oven	for
1	hour
or
until bubbly and lightly brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening, peanut butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients with milk.
(It is best not to add all dry ingredients at once.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet. Dip a fork in water to make a lattice design on the cookies.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until slightly browned on the bottom.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Fry garlic in oil and remove garlic.
Saute chicken (hot oil). Add onion, tomato, parsley, paste and 1 can of water.
Remove chicken when done and take meat off bone and save.
Use juice from chicken to cook rice in.
When rice is almost done, add chicken, capers, pimentos, olives and green peas.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Add 3 cups water and cook until thickens. Cool 2 hours.
Add 9 ounce tub Cool Whip.
Drain 1 can Mandarin oranges and add.

title: blt bites
directions: Cut a thin slice off the top of each tomato.
Scoop out and discard pulp.
Invert the tomatoes on a paper towel to drain.
Mix the rest of ingredients and fill tomatoes.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 16 to 20 tomatoes.

title: pineapple-cream cheese salad
directions: Combine lemon jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix cream cheese and crushed pineapple with juice.
Set in refrigerator until soft.
Add Dream Whip, without vanilla.
Mix into ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sue's sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, celery and onion together in a skillet. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; add the meat mixture and bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 generously.
Delicious with chilled green asparagus!

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Thinly slice the sausage and slowly brown in large heavy saucepan.
Take out sausage and saute onions, celery and green pepper.
Add tomatoes and cook until it looks mushy.
Add sausage back and cook 20 minutes.
Add diced chicken, stock, mushrooms, black pepper, salt and red pepper and cook for 20 minutes.
Add green onion and rice and cook slowly, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: chequer's quiche
directions: Bake in pie crust at 350° for 40 minutes or until custard like consistency.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil all together for 5 minutes.
Set off heat and cool for 5 minutes.
Pour 1 bottle or 1 package of Certo into it.
Blend in. After 5 minutes, pour into jar, while hot.
Wash and boil jars and lids.

title: jack daniels marinade
directions: Mix well and dip meat.
Brush on while grilling.

title: light rolls
directions: Knead dough and let rise twice.
Make into rolls and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: greek collards
directions: Wash collards.
Remove any tough stems.
Cut in small strips. Place in large saucepan in pressure cooker.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook until tender.

title: spiced chiffon cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add water, oil and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Whip egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 325° for 70 minutes.
Immediately invert pan and cool. Remove from pan.

title: hot sausage and pepper sandwiches
directions: Brown garlic and sausage in olive oil.
Add onions and peppers 5 minutes before sausage is done.
Remove sausage and drain all but 1 tablespoon oil.
Cut sausage into 2 inch pieces. Add tomato paste, water and sausage.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Serve on crusty, hearty rolls or as a side dish for a buffet.

title: great grandma's sugar cookies(cake-like sugar cookies)
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and margarine.
Sift dry ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill dough for 2 to 3 hours.
Keep unused dough refrigerated while patting out other small portions on heavily floured board.
Cut with shaped cookie cutters.
Don't pat dough less than 1/4-inch thickness, the thicker the cookie the better cake-like texture.
Let stand on ungreased cookie sheet for 5 minutes before baking.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly but do not beat too much.
Bake in greased, floured, bread pan for about 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk and bread crumbs.
Add to ground beef, salt, pepper and other ingredients.
Mix well to combine.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Fry until brown.
Place cooked meatballs in large pan.
Add 1 bottle barbecue sauce and heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: snappy holiday carrots
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp.
Using a food processor, coarsely shred or thinly slice the carrots.
Add to onion and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
Mix in mayonnaise, horseradish and seasoning.

title: strawberry tapioca jello salad
directions: Boil water.
Add Jell-O and both pudding packages.
Stir and cook until thick and clear.
Cool in ice water and set in refrigerator until thick.
Gently fold in Cool Whip, fruit and marshmallows.

title: barbecue pork (beef)
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Add onion, sprinkles of spices and water.
Cook on low overnight.
Separate bone and fat; mince meat. Clean pot and replace meat.
Add bottle of barbecue sauce and cook on low for 8 hours more.
Stir 2 to 3 times while cooking. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 shredded cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Mix in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Separate rolls into 2 rectangles, pressing together cuts.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips.
Place strips on casserole to form lattice.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Top lattice with rest of cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes more.

title: fruit cobbler(for peach, cherry, apricot or berry)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and boiling water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add fruit.
Put the fruit in baking dish and dot with dough.

title: orange sunbursts
directions: Cut tops off oranges.
Using a grapefruit knife, scoop out pulp.
Chop pulp; mix with dates, coconut and dash of aromatic bitters.
Spoon into orange shells.
Place in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour a little water around oranges.
Bake in slow oven at 325°
for 25 minutes.
Top each orange with a marshmallow. Bake 8 to 10 minutes more until the marshmallows are golden. Makes 5 servings.

title: cajun ham
directions: Line roasting pan with 2 layers of heavy-duty foil.
Place ham in pan.

Poke holes on bottom and top of ham with long-tined fork. Pour hot sauce on bottom and poke with fork so hot sauce penetrates. Turn over and poke holes in top and add hot sauce. Pour Coke over top and close foil over top.
Cook in a 250° oven overnight (8 hours).
Let cook completely.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Line cupcake pans with paper inserts and place a cookie in each.
Put 1 Tbsp. of batter on each cookie.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.
Cool then top each with cherry pie filling.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook cornbread and cool completely.
This can be done a day ahead.
Crumble cornbread into a large bowl; sprinkle with salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and parsley.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados and add remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice in pot pan; add sliced apples and cook about 5 minutes or until apples become tender; take the apples out of pan and set aside.
Reserve the juice!

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix together the last 5 ingredients and pour over the cucumbers, onions and pepper.
Mix well until sugar is dissolved. Put in container and freeze.
After opening, keep refrigerated.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1 cup juice.
Chop cherries.
Stir together gelatins and 2 cups boiling water until completely dissolved.
Stir in reserved cherry juice, sugar, port, and lemon juice.
Stir in cherries.
Lightly spray a 10-cup ring mold or Bundt cake pan with vegetable cooking spray, and pour half of gelatin mixture into mold.
Chill 2 hours or until almost set. Stir together remaining gelatin mixture, cream cheese, and pecans, blending well.
Pour over slightly set gelatin mixture in mold. Chill 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish, if desired.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Toss in buttermilk and eggs.
Beat well and then put in a buttered baking dish and cook at 350° for about 1 hour.
Watch time as sometimes it cooks faster.
Don't overcook. Spoon onto plates, smother with butter and eat.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped pecans, dates and cherries and mix well. Shape into balls using teaspoonful of dough for each.
Crush cornflakes.
Roll each ball of dough in cornflakes and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, cook bacon until brown and crisp. Remove and drain on paper towel; dice or crumble.
In same saucepan, saute chopped onions and potatoes for a couple of minutes; sprinkle with flour.
Add clam juice from cans and bottle, stir and bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring from time to time, until potatoes are soft, about 15 minutes.
Add half-and-half and season to taste.
Add minced clams and heat until simmering.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve immediately.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight for best taste.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, slice and chop fine (or grate) pears.
Put in a heavy pot.
Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let cook down until thick.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes about 30 pints.

title: dill and onion vegetable dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sour cream or yogurt.
Mix in shredded green onion, parsley, dill weed and Beau Monde seasoning.
Chill for an hour to blend flavors.
Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to keep them stiff.
Cream shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar. Add unbeaten egg yolks; beat until creamy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Fold in blueberries.
(Gently shake a bit of the flour called for in the recipe over the blueberries so they won't settle.)
Turn into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch,
milk
and eggs until thick and add vanilla.
Cover with
Saran
Wrap
to
keep from crusting; cool. Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Work together to make crumbs.
Sprinkle half
or	a
little more over bottom of cold crust.
Put cold filling over crumbs.
Put Cool Whip over filling. Sprinkle rest
of	crumbs on Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until defrosted.
Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sandra's deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs and enough water to cover in stainless boiler. Bring to a boil and boil exactly 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour off boiling water.
Cover with cold water and a few pieces of ice.
Let set a few minutes.
Remove shells and slice lengthwise. Remove yolks and put in separate container.
Mash.
To mashed yolks, add seasonings and beat until fluffy.
Refill whites of eggs and garnish with paprika, a sprig of parsley or any desired garnish.
Makes plenty.
They go fast!

title: fancy baked chicken
directions: Melt butter, add cheese, salt and garlic.
Dip chicken into butter mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Spread remaining mixture over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bride's fruit cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add the other ingredients.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.
Place pan of water on shelf below cake and bake until firm.

title: candied apples
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, light cream and butter.
Cook until dissolved (on low heat).
Cook to hard boil stage (don't stir). Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Dip apples and roll in nuts.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix nuts, oleo and flour.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or more.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil; beat in eggs, zucchini and extract.
Add dry ingredients; add raisins and nuts.
Place in a greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones and cut chicken to desired size.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth with onion, celery, salt and pepper, according to directions on package.
Add mushroom soup, pimentos and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and browns slightly.
May top with grated cheese.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten egg yolks.
Add potatoes, vanilla and nutmeg.
Whip egg whites and add to mixture.
Bake in pie shell at 325° for approximately 45 minutes or until done in center.
Test with a toothpick.

title: apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put the apples.
Put the sugars over apples; mix and let stand.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another small bowl, stir together the eggs, oil, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour egg mixture and flour mixture over apples; mix with wooden spoon until well blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(I prefer margarine to "grease" the pan, and I use a mixture of some sugar and cinnamon, instead, to "flour" the pan.)

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and soak in water and lime mixture for 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Put into ice water for 20 minutes, then drain in sink or on paper towels.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good.
Roll into balls the size of a quarter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Be sure to turn.

title: camper's potatoes
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients, dot with oleo (may add small pieces of bacon, if desired).
Cover.
Microwave on "High" for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in iron skillet.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together and pour over oleo.
Then pour peaches with syrup over flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Best if served hot with ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine half can of chow mein noodles with rest of the ingredients.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
(You may top with French fried onions or cheese or both.) Sprinkle the rest of the chow mein noodles on top and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: apricot nut cups
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine into flour with a pastry blender.
Form 24 (1-inch) balls.
Place into mini muffin pan with a ball of dough; press into place with thumbs.
Combine egg, brown sugar, apricot filling and nuts.
Spoon into crusts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt jane's famous lasagna(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare lasagna noodles according to directions; drain and set aside.
Crumble hamburger and fry until brown.
Add chopped onion while browning hamburger.
Add garlic to taste.
Drain hamburger.
Add 1 jar of spaghetti sauce (whatever brand you like) to meat and onion mixture.
Set out 1 package cream cheese and allow it to come to room temperature.
Cut slices of cream cheese.
Add a small amount of meat sauce to bottom of casserole dish, enough to coat.
Layer lasagna noodles; put pieces of cream cheese on the noodles.
(I flatten the cream cheese out and lay on noodles.)
Add meat sauce and continue, ending with meat sauce on top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: Heat soup and milk in pan.
Stir often.
Stir in vegetables; return to boiling.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender. Stir in cheese.
Heat through.
If desired, substitute 16-ounce bag of frozen vegetables.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chuck hines' baked beans
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp and drain well, reserving 1/4 cup bacon fat.
Saute veggies in reserved fat until tender.
Add chuck and brown slightly.
Stir in liquid smoke and barbecue sauce.
Mix well with beans and pour into baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Best ever, a meal in itself.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook brown sugar and cream or evaporated milk to soft-ball stage; beat until creamy.
Flavor with vanilla or maple flavoring. If icing gets too hard, add a little more cream and beat.

title: mandarin orange cake #1
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat on low 30 seconds.
Then on medium 2 minutes.
Put into 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool completely.

title: sandwich spread
