directions: Put vegetables through food grinder; coarse or fine grind as you prefer.
Add salt and let stand 2 hours.
Squeeze out juice. Add vinegar and sugar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add mustard and salad dressing.
Put back on stove and cook 5 minutes longer.
Watch closely, as it scorches easily.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 12 to 14 pints.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Mix sauce together and pour over chicken in electric skillet. Cook for approximately 40 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken after to keep it coated in sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Set in shallow pan; fill pan to 1 inch with hot water. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: skillet chicken cordon bleu
directions: Lightly brown chicken on both sides in skillet.
Cover chicken with ham.
Mix the water, wine and gravy mix together and pour over ham and chicken.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally to keep gravy from sticking. Layer cheese on top and continue cooking until cheese has melted.

title: walnut crest cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add water, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll between hands into (teaspoon) oval shapes (crescents).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.
Roll while warm (carefully) in confectioners sugar.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Put liquids, sugar, salt and pepper in container and shake well. Pour over cucumbers and onions.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place cooked potatoes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine 2 teaspoons melted margarine with flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add liquid from potatoes and milk. Cook until thickened and bubbly, stirring frequently.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix 1 teaspoon margarine, bread crumbs, paprika and thyme; sprinkle over mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil; prick several holes for steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broiled tuna burgers
directions: Mix all together, toast muffins then spread with tuna mixture. Brown under the broiler.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix the pie filling and pineapple together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over top.
Melt margarine and pour over the top; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour; top with Cool Whip.

title: double cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese. On wax paper form into ball. Roll out 1/2 with rolling pin. Place meat layer in pan, cover with cheese. Layer the other 1/2 over the top. Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: asparagus with lemon-parsley sauce
directions: Whirl together parsley, anchovies, lemon juice, chicken broth and capers for about 1 minute or until pureed.
Add the oil and whirl 30 seconds longer; set aside.

title: carrot bars
directions: Blend grated carrots and
oil thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, blending
after
each addition.
Then add remaining ingredients which have been sifted together.
Pour into a 12 x 18-inch
greased pan and bake at
for
about	30
to	35 minutes.
Let cool, then frost and cut into bars.

title: sunshine pudding(easy)
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread in casserole dish.
Sprinkle on sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, lemon and almond extracts; set aside.
Add rolls to scalded milk; let soak a few minutes. Add egg mixture to milk and rolls.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Mix cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle over butter.
Bake at 350° on rack over water 1 hour. Yields 9 servings.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Separate skins from pulp of grapes.
Cook pulp 5 minutes or until softened.
Put through sieve to remove seed.
Add pulp to skins.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add to grapes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Make pastry.
Pour in pastry-lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust and crimp edges.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: aunt ruby's pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to mixture.
Cook in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: orange delight
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Mix well and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
This must be cold before adding whipped cream.
Place can of milk in freezer for 1 hour.
Take out and beat to a stiff peak.
Blend thoroughly with jello mixture.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish or two 6 x 10-inch dishes.
Mix topping of margarine, nuts, coconut and cracker crumbs.
Crumble over top.
Store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: alaska seafood omelet
directions: *If desired 1 cup (about 5 oz.)
Alaska Pink shrimp, Alaska Dungeness, King or Snow crab meat or combination of seafoods may be substituted.

title: finger jello
directions: Stir to dissolve jello mixes in boiling liquid.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 3 hours, until firmly set.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water for ease in lifting out "finger-size" jello squares that you cut.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine strawberries and the
2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, the 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring until combined.
Spray an 8-inch round baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
With lightly floured hands, pat dough into pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for about 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely or serve shortcake warm.

title: creamy taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, gradually stir in sour cream.
Add bean dip and taco seasoning and stir well.
Put into small casserole dish and top with cheddar cheese.
Cover and heat at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: eck's pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans and fill half full. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line baking dish with boiled chicken.
Mix in broth, vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and oleo.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve hot.

title: quick lemon-broccoli rice
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice and lemon juice.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff rice with fork before serving.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of water.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with more cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Combine all ingredients; toss to mix. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Serve cold. Makes about 12 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper and dredge in flour.
Heat shortening in frying pan; brown meat and add onion.
Pour apple juice over meat and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Cut carrots into long, narrow strips.
Slice celery into 1/2-inch chunks.
Core and peel apples; cut in medium slices and place in casserole dish.
Pour stew into vegetable mixture.
Add spices and bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy pasta and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine cream cheese and milk.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt sweet chocolate in double boiler.
Do not boil or overheat.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Whip egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add melted chocolate.
Last, fold in whipped cream and flavorings.

title: tomato appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve in mugs with celery sticks.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add milk and eggs.
Add zucchini, vanilla and orange peel and rest of ingredients.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or shape into loaf.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° (moderate oven) about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and drain off excess fat. Makes 6 servings.

title: irish cake
directions: Simmer raisins in 1 cup of tea for 15 minutes in covered pot. Add sugars, applesauce and butter until melted.
Let it cool.
Add 2 well beaten eggs.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients.
Mix well and add to mixture.
Grease a tube pan and sprinkle with flour. Shake out excess.
Cook for 2 hours at 325° covered with foil.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Cook lemon pudding as directed on box.
Add the lime gelatin (dry).
Add 1 cup cold water; stir.
Add to this the drained crushed pineapple.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup flaked coconut into prepared pan.
Mix one German chocolate cake mix by directions and pour over nuts and coconut. Melt one stick margarine and 8 ounces cream cheese; add 1 pound of confectioners sugar and whisk until smooth.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "no-bake" oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, quick oatmeal and chocolate chips.

title: two-tone chocolate fudge(from the sunday wisconsin state journal)
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, melt the semi-sweet chips with 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup nutmeats. Spread into an aluminum foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
In another saucepan, over low heat, melt milk chocolate chips with remaining milk, cream and vanilla.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining nutmeats.
Spread over first fudge layer in square pan.
Chill for about 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto a cutting board. Peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered and at room temperature.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: chili mac
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery.
Add ground meat and lightly brown.
Add chili powder and 2 (6 ounce) cans tomato paste with water.
Boil, then add raw macaroni.
Cook until macaroni is done. Add more water if necessary.
Makes 8 servings.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Saute onion, oil and ground beef until brown and crumbly.
Make sauce of corn, salt, rosemary, oregano and marjoram.
Combine tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Pour 1/2 of sauce mixture over meat; simmer 5 minutes.
In bottom of large flat cake pan or electric skillet, arrange 6 tortillas.
Pour meat mixture over top. Put 1/2 of cheese over meat.
Cover with remaining tortillas (6); next put on rest of meat mixture, then rest of sauce.
Top with rest of cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
(Electric frypan at 240°.)
If prepared earlier in day, allow 1 hour to cook.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine honey, mustard, lemon juice, poppy seed and pepper.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place chicken, bone side up, on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 15 minutes.
Turn.
Continue broiling for 10 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and sugar together; pack into an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 375° and cool. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; beat well.
Blend in the whipped cream.
Pour mixture over cooled crumb crust; refrigerate until firm.
Pour cherry pie filling over cream filling. Refrigerate and serve.

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Mix together the sugar, cocoa, corn syrup, vinegar and salt thoroughly in a heavy saucepan.
Add butter; cook slowly, stirring constantly, until the sugar dissolves.
Bring the mixture to a boil; add evaporated milk slowly, so boiling does not stop.
Cook mixture over low fire, stirring occasionally, until it reaches 265°.
Mix into 2-quarts freshly popped corn.
Dip out large spoonfuls and make into balls, first wetting the hands in cold water or rubbing them lightly with butter.
One must work quickly. Yield: About 20 (4-inch) balls.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: No milk, baking powder, soda or salt needed.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Beat all together and serve cold.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Do not use juice.
Mix ingredients and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour and begin to beat butter and flour.
Add gradually and blend until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll dough into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and set aside.
Cut up lettuce.
Mix in tomatoes, onions, cheese and beef.
Pour dressing over to taste.
Mix well, then add chips.
Makes a big bowl.

title: microwave barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in microwave dish and add sauce.
Season to taste. Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken and add sauce.
Cook on High another 10 minutes or more, depending on size of chicken.

title: chocolate leaves
directions: Place chocolate chips in ovenproof bowl in warm oven, about 150°, leaving oven door slightly open.
When chocolate has begun to melt yet still retains shape somewhat, remove from oven and beat until smooth.
Pull a single leaf upside down over surface of chocolate.
Tap leaf against bowl to remove excess.
Place chocolate side up on baking sheet.
Chill in refrigerator.
When chocolate is chilled and hardened, peel off rose leaf.
Can store in airtight container in refrigerator for several days.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peach honey
directions: Process peaches in food processor or blender until smooth. Combine peaches and honey in saucepan.
Mix together the cornstarch, lemon juice and water; add to peach puree and heat until thick and bubbly.
Stir in almond extract.
Use with Peach Stuffed Chicken recipe, or over ice cream or pancakes.
Makes eight 2-ounce servings.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in a medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Stir constantly, then drain well.
Line bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage, then cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until set.
Let stand 5 minutes after removing from oven.
Be sure center of dish is not too watery. Cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Slowly add flour. When all is combined, mix in 7-Up.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas until you get 1 1/2 inches from top.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Pour into bowl over wafers and bananas.
Slide a butter knife around sides and a few places on top to allow pudding to go to the bottom.
Let cool in the refrigerator for 1 hour or more.
Then eat and enjoy!

title: cornbread salad
directions: I use a can of Oscar Mayer real bacon pieces.

title: fast baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until brown; add onion and cook until done.
Then add mustard, ketchup, molasses and brown sugar.
Cook until bubbly, then add beans and cook 5 minutes more.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Bake
in 9 x 13-inch Corning Ware.
Seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix following directions on box.
Makes four layers.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding water last.
Water aides in mixing, but do not use too much.

title: italian salsa
directions: Thoroughly drain tomatoes, peppers, and artichoke hearts; and then chop.

title: jackie's potluck casserole
directions: In a pan, brown the onion, garlic and meat in oil.
Add the tomatoes, chili flakes, water, noodles and seasoning.
Cook until noodles are cooked.
You can add any fresh, canned or leftover vegetables.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut tenderloin into 1 1/2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside. Drain pineapple, reserving juice in small bowl.
To juice, add ketchup, water, soy sauce, pepper and ginger; stir until smooth. Heat oil in a large skillet or wok on high; stir-fry pork and onion for 5 to 7 minutes or until pork is no longer pink.
Stir pineapple juice mixture.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add tomatoes, rice and sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cheese, then stuff peppers.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: deviled crab-saint helena delight
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour;
add milk and cool until it thickens.
Add slightly beaten egg yolk and shredded crab meat and seasonings.
Cook
minutes.
Stir in onion, lemon juice and red and
green	peppers.
Fill crab or scallop shells with mixture. Sprinkle bread
crumbs.
Bake
in hot oven until top is brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Stirring frequently, cook the first 5 ingredients until beef is browned. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mock baked potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes in 1-inch chunks.
Boil in salted water until done.
Drain well.
Mix oleo and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and toss lightly.
Season with pepper and more salt, if necessary.
Pour potatoes into glass baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle green onion, cheese and bacon bits over potatoes.
Cover with foil and place in a 350° oven until cheese is slightly melted (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once; stir just until the mixture is evenly moist. Fold in raisins and cranberries. Spoon into a greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until done. Cool on wire rack.

title: crab and shrimp hot dish
directions: In a buttered 2-quart casserole dish, combine the rice, green pepper, celery, onion and water chestnuts.
In a bowl, combine mayonnaise and tomato juice.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Pour half of the mixture over rice.
Arrange shrimp and crab around edge, leaving a hole in center.
Pour rest of liquid over everything. Put almonds and cheese in center.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry supreme gelatin
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup water.
Add cherry pie filling and chill until set.

title: baked eggs
directions: Put the desired number of eggs in a shallow baking dish or pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with cream. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Can bake biscuits at the same time.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain.
Arrange broccoli in a lightly greased 1-quart casserole. Place ham slices over broccoli.
Set casserole aside.

title: strawberry-rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch; gradually stir into rhubarb mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: deer roast
directions: Place the roast in an oven roasting bag.
Put the bacon across the roast.
Add the onions, potatoes, carrots and mushrooms. Sprinkle with the Worcestershire sauce and 7 Seasons. Slice the butter on top of the vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Take out of the oven and add the mushroom soup. Bake at 150° for 30 minutes.

title: nut roll(strudel)
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in bowl sugar, butter, milk and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Blend in eggs and yeast.
Gradually blend in flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until light.
Divide into 3 or 4 parts.
Roll out, spread with Nut Filling (or poppy seed filling).
Roll like jelly roll.
Put on baking pans.
Let rise again.
Bake in 350° oven until done (about 35 minutes).

title: caraway bread
directions: In a 2-quart mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
Stir in raisins, caraway seed and orange peel.
Beat buttermilk, egg and baking soda to blend in a small bowl.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients, blending only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cook for 10 to 11 minutes or until dough is firm.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Grate cheese and set aside.
Mix macaroni (drained) and cooked meat.
Add pizza sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, garlic salt, onion salt and oregano. Place 1/2 mixture in buttered casserole.
Top with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Slice pepperoni thin and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: In a large bowl beat egg.
Stir in 1/3 c. soup, bread crumbs, salt & pepper.
Add beef, mix gently.
Shape into 6 oval patties. Brown in skillet over medium heat for 3-4 minutes on each side. Remove & set aside.
In the skillet combine flour & water until smooth.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard & remaining soup.
Bring to a boil & stir for 2 minutes.
Return patties to skillet, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple slices, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Cut pineapple slices into quarters; set pineapple and juice aside.
On waxed paper, mix flour and salt; use to coat chicken breasts.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken breasts until golden and fork-tender, about 10 minutes, turning once.
Remove chicken breasts to warm platter; keep warm.

title: creamy ham-and-chicken medley
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add mushrooms and cook until tender, stirring constantly.
Remove from saucepan; set aside.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix oleo and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the milk.
Put in bread pan and bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Fry bacon.
Drain and crumble. Add all ingredients.
Cook in slow cooker 4 to 5 hours.

title: splattered spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix, tomato sauce, sugar, garlic, onion and basil; simmer. You can add browned ground meat if desired. A jar of Prego spaghetti sauce adds a good flavor and and makes a larger amount. Serve over cooked and drained spaghetti.

title: dough for fatayer or pita bread
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Melt Crisco over low heat and add warm water to melted Crisco.
Add water and dissolved dry yeast and sugar; pour over flour and mix well.
Make a soft dough.
Add more flour if needed.
Knead well until dough is soft but not sticky. Add flour if needed for sticky dough.
Cover with plastic until dough doubles in size (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Divide into equal pieces.
Shape round like a grapefruit.
Set on a floured cloth and let rest approximately 1 hour.
Flatten dough and roll and cut with 4-inch cutter.

title: old fashioned spice cake
directions: Mix milk and vinegar; let set.
Beat vinegar mixture and remaining ingredients in a bowl on medium speed for 30 seconds. Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in a bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coke to boiling point; pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla, salt and marshmallows.
Batter will be thin and marshmallows will float on top.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix in skillet and bring to a boil. Turn down and simmer for 3 minutes. Stuff tortillas with apple pie filling that has been sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar. Roll tortillas and place in baking dish. Pour sugar mixture over tortillas; allow to sit for 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line cool baking pie shell with berries.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Add red food coloring.
Pour glaze over berries.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In an iron skillet, put oleo, dates, white sugar and egg; cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Rice Krispies, vanilla and nut meats.
Turn off heat and while still warm, take by teaspoons and roll in flake coconut or powdered sugar.
Put on wax paper to harden.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco, eggs, sour cream and bananas.
Sift soda with flour and salt.
Stir into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Serve with fresh apple sections.

title: double orange sweet potato
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut a lengthwise groove into each potato.
Drip the orange juice into the grooves and fill each groove with pineapple sections.
Wrap with aluminum foil and bake until tender, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with curry or nutmeg if desired.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Put thawed hash browns in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Heat half and half, margarine and salt in a saucepan. Do not boil.
Pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: strawberry flavored corn
directions: Put the popped corn in a large, buttered roaster.
Boil margarine, sugar and syrup for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Just before you remove it from heat, add the Jell-O.
When Jell-O is dissolved, remove from heat and add salt and soda.
Pour over corn and bake at 250° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: judy's simplified buckeyes
directions: Gather and dry such herbs as you may be able to obtain such as sage, sweet marjoram, lemon thyme, winter savory, sweet basil, celery seed, chives, etc.
Powder these in a blender and place in closed jars for use in cooking.
Season gravies, soups, breadings for steaks and chops, salads and etc.

title: salad for company
directions: Toss all together in large bowl.
Serve with Sweet Onion Dressing, or the dressing of your choice.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients except sugar and celery for 3 hours.
Add sugar and cook 1 hour.
Add celery and cook 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars immediately.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs and butter together.
Add vanilla and sugar; mix well.
Add flour, cocoa and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Roll out half of pastry for bottom crust.
Line a 9-inch pie plate.
Crush 1/2 cup of the berries.
Combine with sugar, tapioca and salt.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add remaining berries.
Pour into pastry shell; dot with butter or margarine.
Roll out remaining pastry; adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges; cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.
Serve pie warm.

title: quick 'n' easy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet and drain.
Mix all ingredients except French fried onions in a large bowl.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Add French fried onions and bake 10 to 15 minutes more. Makes 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad no. 3
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: grilled corned beef
directions: In stock pot, place corned beef, bay leaves, chilies, cinnamon sticks, peppercorns, garlic and onion and cover with water.
Boil for 4 to 5 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and set aside. When corned beef is removed from pot and still hot, rub remaining ingredient mixture all over.
Place on grill and cook until crunchy, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peggy's famous peanut brittle
directions: Cook until it starts to boil, then add peanuts and cook until it turns dark.
Add soda.
Pour on buttered foil.
Let cool, then break up in pieces.
Best to cook in iron skillet.

title: italian snack bites
directions: Microwave Directions:
On a 9-inch microwave-proof plate, combine cereal, pepper, dressing and Italian seasoning; toss to coat well.
Microwave at High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until hot; stir.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave at High for 30 to 40 seconds or until cheese melts. Serve at once.

title: baked chicken that makes its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Arrange chicken in a single layer with skin down in melted butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken. Bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes longer, until tender.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat. Combine evaporated milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add onions and mushrooms to chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover dish with foil.
Return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
Great over rice.

title: marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
(You can use the blender to mix ingredients.)
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.
Keep a long time refrigerated.
Great on London Broil steak.
Marinate meat overnight in sauce.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage and drain.
Combine with oregano, garlic and sauce and put in skillet; add cheese.
Stir until melted and then cool.
Spread on bread.
May be stored in refrigerator until ready to use. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread is enough for two loaves.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla and cream together. Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, sugars, corn syrup and eggs. Stir until smooth. Add vanilla. Sift together soda, salt, flour and oatmeal. Stir into butter mixture. Stir in M&M's and chocolate chips. Put 1/4 cup dough on cookie sheet for each cookie. Flatten each cookie lightly. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix for 1 minute.
Drop with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Don't brown them.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: piperade (open-faced omelet with peppers, tomatoes and ham)(france)
directions: In a
heavy
8 to 10-inch skillet, heat 1/4 cup of oil. When the
oil
is
very hot, stir in the onions and garlic and cook over
moderate heat, stirring frequently for 5 minutes or until they are soft but not browned.
Stir in the green pepper strips and cook, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes or until the peppers
are barely tender.
Drain the tomatoes and stir them into
the skillet along with the basil and Tabasco. Increase the heat
and
cook, stirring constantly, for 2 to 3 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.	Cover the skillet lightly
to keep
the
Piperade
mixture warm and set aside.

title: cherry top cheese cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cake mix, 1 egg, 1 cup milk, cream cheese, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 1/4 cup oil.
Blend remaining cake mix, 1 egg and remaining oil.
Line baking dish with the mixture; pat down flat.
Pour in cream cheese mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool; top with cherry pie filling and refrigerate.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs and beat. Mix in flour and baking powder, adding milk alternately.
Add vanilla and pour in 2 round greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover first layer with pineapple and top second layer with Boiled Frosting.

title: turtle cheese cake
directions: Press crushed cookies and melted butter or margarine into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Pour warmed caramel dip over chocolate crust; sprinkle pecans over dip.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until smooth.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, at low to medium speed until well blended.
Add melted chocolate chips and mix until well mixed.

title: scalded lettuce
directions: Put in heavy pan and cook thick.
Let cool.
Pour over lettuce and onions.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form balls bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 56.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order, stirring just enough to combine. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Especially good sliced thinly and spread with softened cream cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over broccoli.
Slice hard-boiled eggs and lay on top of broccoli.
Cover eggs and broccoli with 2 cups of shredded Cheddar cheese.
In separate bowl, mix 1 tablespoon of milk with can of mushroom soup.
Layer on top of casserole.

title: twinkie salad
directions: Slice Twinkies	in
half; put in oblong dish with cream up. Then
slice bananas, then crushed pineapple.
Fix pudding like the box says
to
do.
After
it is thick, add Cool Whip, then put on top.
You can put nuts on top if you like.

title: fancy franks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients to make sauce.
Simmer sauce until jelly is melted.
Saute sausage and combine with sauce; also add pineapple.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Drop in Ritz crackers. Do not stir.
Boil 2 minutes, then pour in unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put crust on top and bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: brown sausage, drain off fat. Combine with rice, consomme, onion and mushrooms in a 9 x 13 dish. Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Stir gently before serving.

title: country style ribs with sauerkraut
directions: Brown ribs on all sides in a Dutch oven or stock pot pan. When well browned, remove from pan and drain off fat.
Add sauerkraut to the pan; add meat and rest of ingredients and cook until meat is done.
Take out meat from the sauerkraut mixture and remove bone, fat and gristle.
Tear meat into bite size pieces and return to pan.
Continue to simmer for several hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix
jello,
water, lemon juice and rind and salt.
Let partially set
or
jell.
Whip
ice
cold milk.
Add sugar and fold in
the
jello.
Put layer of crushed wafers in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Add jello mixture after beaten stiff and top with more crushed wafers.

title: girdle busting cake
directions: Mix together and put into a lightly-greased and floured 13 x 9 1/4 x 2-inch pan.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken(serves 4)
directions: Dip washed and dried chicken in melted butter.
Dredge in bowl of dressing mix, cheese and crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in well-greased baking dish at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange drained fruits over crust.

title: spring rhubarb cobbler
directions: For rhubarb sauce, combine the sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon. Add rhubarb and water.
Cook and stir until mixture is boiling; cook 1 minute more.
Pour into a baking dish; dot with margarine. Place in a hot 400° oven while preparing biscuits.

title: chow chow
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook 1 hour.
Put into sterilized jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: weight watchers' giant peanut butter breakfast cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients except water, then add water, a teaspoon at a time, to make thick dough.
Shape into a giant cookie and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each one.
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Bake at 375° for 90 minutes.

title: cabbage and polish sausage
directions: Cut cabbage and boil.
Cut sausage in large pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle a little red pepper to taste.
Cook about 1 hour on medium heat.
Turn down to low heat.
Cook 1 hour and let simmer on low heat.

title: coconut willie
directions: Mix in blender with crushed ice.
Serve in coconut shell cup or tall Collins glass.
Garnish with orchid, pineapple and mint leaves.
Serve with 2 straws.

title: almond toffee cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add cake mix.
Beat in eggs.
Add water.
Mix in toffee bits and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes before removing from pan. Do not over bake.

title: kolache
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand 2 minutes.
In another large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add yeast mixture. Add flour, a little at a time, until smooth.
Pat a little vegetable oil on dough and let stand 20 minutes.
Work dough 1 minute.
On a floured surface, spoon out 1 tablespoonful of dough; with floured hands, roll dough into a ball and put on greased pan. Press center of dough.
Place 1 teaspoon of fruit and top with Cheese Filling.

title: a favorite casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine (or Pam) in a pan. Add ground turkey, seasoned salt, oregano, garlic, sugar, tomato sauce, chopped tomatoes, mushrooms and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam, add 8 ounces uncooked egg noodles.
Cover with all sauce mixture and top with 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese (low skim).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Prepare ground meat, chop onion, grate cheese and chop jalapeno peppers; set aside.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, salt, soda, corn and bacon drippings.

title: easy bar-b-que chicken
directions: Combine in crock-pot and cook on low for 6-8 hrs.

title: kid's kobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 2-quart deep casserole or baking dish and melt in oven.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Blend lightly; batter will be slightly lumpy. Pour into center of melted butter.
Top with fruit and whatever juices remain in can after draining.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8. Serve cobbler warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Enjoy.

title: my own sour cream pecan pie
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, beat eggs well. Stir in sour cream. Add corn syrup, maple syrup, vanilla, sugar, salt and butter; mix well. Stir in pecans; pour in pastry shell (unbaked). Bake in preheated 400° oven until crust is brown and filling is slightly puffy, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: sweet-sour meat loaf
directions: Add all ingredients, then mix chili sauce and eggs together with meat.
Bake at 375° in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: fiesta rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook pepper and onion until tender, stirring often. Add V-8 juice and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Uncover; cook 5 minutes more or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally. Stir in cheese.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and measure liquid; add enough water to make 1 cup and add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in blueberries and drained pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart flat pan, cover and put in refrigerator until set firm.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: hot milk pound cake
directions: Melt butter in milk in a small saucepan. Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add milk and butter to batter and beat for 2 minutes. Grease and flour a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yellow cake with caramel icing
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.
Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir mixture into crackers and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix box of cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
It will look like a glob; spread into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then mix box powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs; beat together until creamy.
Pour over.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Put in refrigerator.

title: kentucky's best rolls
directions: Start with yeast and sugar; add warm water and then Crisco. Scald milk and pour into mixture.
Add some of the warm milk to the eggs; stir quickly.
Add the eggs, sugar, salt and cold water. Start with 1 cup of flour and keep adding until you have a good dough.
Sometimes it will only take 5 cups flour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: flour frosting
directions: Cook until very thick the flour and milk, then let cool.
Beat sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Add flour mixture; cream, very good, until right texture for frosting.

title: cranberry punch for the kids!
directions: Chill juice and lemon soda until ready to use.
Pour cranberry juice into large punch bowl.
Add raspberry sherbet by putting scoops of it into the juice.
Over the sherbet, pour lemon soda until punch is frothy and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: creamy caesar salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Delicious on romaine lettuce with bacon, coddled eggs and croutons.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Place green pepper, onion and pineapple on paper towel to absorb liquid.
Blend ingredients well.
Refrigerate and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans, if desired.
(I made it into 2 balls.)
Great for parties.

title: italian tomato rolls
directions: Combine the 1 teaspoon sugar, the warm water and the yeast in a small bowl. Stir to mix and then set aside until mixture becomes bubbly.
In large bowl, combine the remaining sugar, pizza sauce, water, egg, melted butter, salt, and basil.
Mix well. Add 1 cup flour and the yeast. Mix well.
Gradually add the remaining flour until a moderately firm dough is formed.
Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until it is no longer sticky. This sometimes take 4 to 5 minutes.
Place in a large oiled bowl and turn the dough so that all surfaces are oiled.
Cover and allow to rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch down the dough and pinch off portions about the size of a golf ball.
Roll into balls (or shape as desired) and place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover with towel and set in warm place until doubled.
This will probably take about 45 minutes. Bake at 400 degrees for about 8 to 10 minutes or until rolls start to brown on top. Brush generously with butter or margarine.
Place a piece of aluminum foil loosely over the top of the rolls and continue baking for an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until rolls are fully cooked.
Remove from oven and brush again with melted butter.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth. Sift flour, salt and soda; add to first mixture and mix well. Roll dough and mash with fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: doughnuts number 2
directions: Sift flour
with
salt and soda.
Add sugar to eggs and milk. Beat
thoroughly
until
sugar
is dissolved.
Then add melted butter
and
flour (enough to make a soft dough).
Stir with knife.
Roll
1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and fry in hot oil at 375°.

title: wild duck bohemian
directions: Cut orange peels into strips, about 1/4-inch wide.
Poke holes into the ducks and force the peels into the holes.
Completely cover the ducks with remaining orange peels.
Cook the wild rice in 1-quart of water with 1 teaspoon salt for 40 minutes.
Drain off unabsorbed water and dry the rice on a paper towel.
Add onion, pepper, celery, mushrooms (sliced), pepper and melted butter to the rice and mix well.
Stuff the ducks with this dressing and roast for 2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate pepper cookies
directions: Combine and sift together all dry ingredients.
Place in large bowl and make a well in the middle.
Add oil, milk and mix thoroughly until dough is firm.
Bread off pieces size of walnuts and press lightly onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening.
Add enough cold water to make ingredients combine.
Roll pastry 1/4-inch thick and cut in 8 squares.

title: pan fried trout
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Careful not to overheat or burn butter.
Spread about 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard in cavity of trout.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll each trout in flour to coat.
When butter is melted, but not changed color, place trout in heavy iron skillet being careful that the fish do not touch each other.
Cook on one side until golden brown. Turn and cook other side the same.
Remove fish to heated dish.
Repeat until all trout are cooked.
Add about 1/2 stick butter to skillet and melt.
Then squeeze juice of one lemon into skillet.
Stir well and pour a small amount of liquid over each trout as served. Dee-lish!
The secret to good trout is to cook slowly about 8 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Cook meat with onion and pepper.
Add soup and mix together. Put into pie crust.
Add top crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: goldie oldie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk. Mix well; stir in flavoring and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or 8-inch pan.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Knead wheat germ into pizza dough. Spread dough to 1/2-inch thickness onto a nonstick baking pan coated with cooking spray, sprinkled with corn meal.
In bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, garlic, oregano and thyme.
Spread mixture onto crust.
Top with vegetables.
Coat with cooking spray.
Bake 18 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese; sprinkle edges with 1 tablespoon wheat germ.
Bake 2 minutes more.

title: layered sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets until done.
Peel and cut into slices.
Place half the slices in a layer in buttered casserole dish.
Add half the brown sugar.
Dot with half the butter and add a layer of cranberry sauce.
Repeat layers.
Pour orange juice over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until heated through.

title: fruit dip
directions: Stir together until well blended.
Serve with pieces of fresh fruit (apples, pears, strawberries, bananas, etc.).

title: tex-mex
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Put 1 cup noodles in bottom of ungreased casserole.
Mix other ingredients; put on top of noodles.
Cover with remaining noodles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Whip egg white and water. Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt. Add to egg white mixture.
Pour over pecans and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles (per directions).
Drain.
Add tuna (drained), golden mushroom soup and mushroom pieces (drained).
Stir all together.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled soda crackers.
Dot with dabs of margarine.
Put in oven or microwave for about 5 or 10 minutes to melt margarine and brown.
Serve.

title: dirty cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies fine and put half in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix milk, cream cheese, instant pudding and vanilla.
Pour over Oreos and put the remaining crushed cookies over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Save small amount of cookies to decorate top of dessert.
Sprinkle lightly over Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Can be decorated with gummy worms.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook berries and 1/2 cup sugar until dissolved.
Put margarine in baking dish and melt in a 350° oven.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour into margarine, then add fruit. Bake until brown.

title: pasta house salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces.
Toss with artichoke hearts, red onion and pimento.
Whisk together the oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over lettuce and toss.
Goes well with pasta.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Cook peas according to package; drain.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Break bread into small pieces and add milk, then beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Put catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry compote
directions: Place water and sugar in a medium saucepan and heat over medium-high heat until sugar is dissolved, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in the pears and cranberries and cook until the cranberries just begin to pop, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Alternate layers of beans and onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, milk and marjoram.
Pour over beans and onions.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: strata
directions: Mix eggs, milk and mustard and pour over remaining ingredients in greased 8 x 12-inch glass pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Halve the pineapple chunks in a large bowl.
Peel and cut up the orange and add.
As you cut up additional fruits, toss into this mixture to prevent browning.

title: unexpected company
directions: Drain potatoes; mix everything, add seasoning to taste.
Top casserole with biscuit dough, corn muffin mix or slice can biscuits diagonally.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix the sugar, salt and flour. Gradually add 1 1/2 cups milk gradually; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Continue to cook for 3 minutes. Add some of the mixture to 1 slightly beaten egg yolk while stirring. Add hot mixture and cook for 1 minute. Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and cool. Slice bananas into baked shell and pour pudding over them.

title: fig-strawberry preserves
directions: Cook mashed figs and sugar 20 or 25 minutes.
When ready, add 2 small boxes jello, cook until dissolved.
Pour into jars; seal.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan and stir in milk, egg yolks and pumpkin.
Stir over medium heat until mix bubbles. Remove and cool.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar and beat until still.
Fold pumpkin mix with whipped cream.
Pile into crust and chill for 1 hour.
Whip 2 pints whipping cream.
Fill pastry bags and decorate top of pie.

title: nut bread
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: instant lasagna for one
directions: Soak lasagna noodles in cold water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Place 1/2 cup Ricotta cheese in center of each noodle, roll, seam side down, in small casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce and 2 tablespoons Mozzarella.
Cook, covered with wax paper, in microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: cape cod clam boil
directions: Peel onions, shuck corn and scrub potatoes.
Put all ingredients, except clams and lobsters, in individual cheesecloth bags (corn in one, onion in another, etc.).
In a very large pot, barely cover bottom with water, just enough to make steam.
Put clams on bottom, all bagged ingredients next, lobsters on top. Sprinkle with Old Bay Seasoning.
Put one uncooked potato on top[. Cover and cook about one hour.
When potatoes on top is done, boil should be ready.
Serve with melted butter.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Place ground beef and onions in deep skillet.
Cook over medium heat until beef has lost it's pinkness and onions are wilted.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain off any excess grease.
Serve warm over hot dogs.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream the butter .
Add sugar. Add egg.
Beat well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and applesauce while mixing.
Stir in raisins.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Goes great with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, pie spice, baking powder and salt together.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil, then stir in pumpkin.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mint ice cream pies
directions: Combine cake mix, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat until moistened.
Spread batter in 2 greased 9-inch plates.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Stir ice cream until smooth and spread in pie shells.
Heat frosting until softened. Spread on top of ice cream.
Freeze until firm.

title: margaret's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix and bake cornbread as directed on box.
Crumble cornbread; add onion, eggs, gizzards and celery as desired.
Gradually add broth until mixture is moist to your desired texture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until onion is tender.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake in unbaked shell.	Makes two pies.

title: shrimp orleans
directions: Saute the onion until tender in a small amount of oil.
Add parsley, celery and garlic. Cook 3 minutes. Add shrimp and cook until pink and tender. Stir in sour cream and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until mixture comes to a slow boil.
Season to taste and simmer for 5 minutes. Add peas; simmer for 2 more minutes. Serve in patty shells or in French bread with 1/4 of the middle of the bread removed (to resemble a canoe).

title: dressed-up potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake potatoes until done.
Scoop potato from shells, saving shells.
In medium bowl, mash potatoes with either dressing.
Stir in cheese and ham.
Refill shells.
Bake 15 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: boiled icing
directions: Break egg whites into mixing bowl.
Put sugar, water and corn syrup into a small saucepan; stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil rapidly until the syrup can be formed into soft ball when
a little is dropped into cold water (238°).
Remove from stove.
Beat egg whites quickly until stiff.
Continue beating, while pouring the hot syrup in a fine stream over the egg whites.
Add flavoring and continue beating until the mixture is stiff enough to spread on cake.

title: simple bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add water.
Make small round portions.
Roll small balls out like pancakes.
Fry pancakes on griddle pan (no oil) for 3 minutes and turn.
Place in broiler at 350°.
They are done when they pop up like a pita (5 to 10 minutes).
Fill with tuna and cheese or spread with butter and honey.
Yummy!

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss together lightly the sugar, flour and cornmeal. Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth and thoroughly blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: french toast
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; beat slightly.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture quickly.
Drain and coat both sides with cornflake crumbs.
Place on buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans or cookie sheets.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes. Turn slices and bake until hot, crisp and browned, 6 to 8 minutes. Serve hot with favorite syrup or fruit sauce.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: common senses squash casserole
directions: Boil squash on medium heat in 2 to 3 cups of water; drain after squash is cooked to tender.
Blend in all ingredients except 1 package of shredded Cheddar cheese for topping.
Be sure all is well blended before topping with Cheddar cheese.
Place in a Pam-sprayed pan.
Bake on 350° to 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is brown to your likeness.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 5 day rotten coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in two layers. Split the layers.
Mix together the sour cream, sugar, coconut and vanilla and spread between the layers.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pink salad
directions: Bring to boil crushed pineapple.
Add box of Jell-O; cool. Add both containers Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion.
While they saute, mix beef, flour and seasonings (paprika, pepper and salt).
Add to onion.
Mix and cook until beef is done.
Add soup.
Stir and cook 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add sour cream and blend into meat mixture.
Serve over top of cooked rice or noodles.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: For sauce, in a saucepan melt butter, then blend in flour. Cook over moderate heat and slowly stir in milk.
Season with salt and cayenne.
Continue cooking until sauce is smooth and boiling. Reduce heat and add cheese, stirring, until cheese is blended. Add green pepper/pimento mixture.
Stir and remove from heat.

title: tomato-green bean casserole
directions: Cook the beans in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt shortening in a saucepan.
Add onions and saut until golden.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour 3/4 of the mixture over beans and cover with tomato slices.
Add remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: irresistibly light hot rolls
directions: Scald milk; add butter, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs to the milk mixture, then add yeast mixture.
Gradually add flour, mixing well after each addition. Allow dough to rise in a warm place.
After approximately 2 hours, punch down and shape into small balls to make cloverleaf rolls. Let rolls rise 1 hour in well-greased cupcake tins.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
This recipe makes about 30 cloverleaf rolls.

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: Mix and make into 1 big ball or 2 small ones.
(Leave cheese until last.)
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll ball in cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Press half
of
crushed cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix
pudding
and milk until thick.
Mix butter and cream cheese, then
add
powdered sugar.
Add pudding gradually, mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cookies.
Sprinkle remaining cookies on top and freeze.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks, Crisco and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly. Heat until mixture comes to a boil (about 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until frosting is thick. Cool 15 minutes.
Spread on top of layers.

title: celebrity fudge
directions: Break sweet chocolate into pieces.
Place in large bowl with chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Bring sugar, salt, butter and milk to a boil, stirring occasionally, for 6 minutes. Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 3/4 pounds.

title: maggie mae boone's caramel cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add extract.
Sift together cream of tartar, soda, salt and flour.
Stir in milk then flour mixture, a small amount at a time.
Put in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll out and cut to desired shapes.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.
Ovens vary so it is best to test to see when done.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: To Freeze Bananas:
Peel and wrap in plastic wrap.
Place in freezer for 12 hours.

title: mango muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 24 cupcake tins.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add mangos, oil, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add nuts/coconut if used.
Pour into muffin tins and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Can also bake in small foil bread pans to use as gifts.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix all together and roll into small balls.
Roll the balls in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla. Add eggs. Beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together and place in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons butter; blend in the 2 tablespoons flour and cook until smooth.
Stir in the 1/2 cup milk, gradually.
Bring to a boil.
Add seasoning, the 1 can soup and the 1/2 pound cheese. Heat, stirring constantly.
Cool and stir in the 1 cup sour cream. Place cooked broccoli in a buttered casserole.
Top with mushrooms and chicken.
Pour sauce over; then sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs, then mix flour and vanilla flavoring. Add apples, coconut and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix first six ingredients until cream cheese is melted down, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken; put 1 tablespoon of mixture in a crescent roll.
Fold up and seal.
Roll in melted butter, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place on ungreased jelly roll pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes about 15 to 20 roll-ups.
Serve with gravy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease large Bundt pan.
Pour nuts evenly into pan.
Cut biscuits into squares.
Roll each piece in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Arrange biscuits in pan.
Melt oleo and add brown sugar.
Pour over sugar and biscuits.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, depending on size of biscuits.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all together and beat 4 minutes.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 20 minutes and remove from pan and continue to cool.

title: "holiday gift cake"
directions: Thoroughly blend softened cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition. Gradually add 2 cups flour with cherries and 1/2 cup nuts.
Fold into batter.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix salt, sugar, cornstarch, water and vinegar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over beets.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Add butter and reheat.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Saute onion in butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute and add water and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in bouillon granules, and next 5 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and chill.
Shape mixture into croquettes and roll in cracker crumbs.
Pour 3 to 4 inches of vegetable oil in electric frying pan and heat to 350°.
Fry chicken until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with cream sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mrs. dot's pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook in greased cake pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: linguine with sauce verde
directions: Process, except pasta and almonds, in a food blender.
Heat to taste.
Cook pasta as directed on package.
Serve linguine with sauce and almonds, tossed to coat.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 320 calories.

title: ozark mountain apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Stir alternately with apples and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ruth's pecan balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla. Add flour, salt and pecans. Form in balls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy-does-it fruit salad
directions: Heat 1 cup of juice to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
Pour into 1 quart mold. Chill until firm. Unmold on salad greens.
Serves 6.

title: holiday chutney
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; simmer for 15-20 minutes or until apple is tender and mixture thickened. Cool completely. Store in refrigerator. Serve over block of cream cheese with crackers or as a condiment with pork, ham, or chicken. Makes 3 cups.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Beat all ingredients except carrots and frosting in bowl on low speed, 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in carrots and pecans. Pour into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together peas, corn and green onion; cover and chill several hours.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together except blueberries.
Take 1/2 mixture and crumble on cookie sheet.
Lay on blueberries.
Crumble on 1/2 of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hoagie salad
directions: On a plate, tear up the lettuce into small pieces.
Top with tomato, onion and sliced olives.
Cut up the salami, Provolone cheese and ham into bite size pieces and add.
Drizzle with olive oil and some of the juice from ripe olives.
Season to taste with garlic salt, pepper and dried oregano or Italian seasoning. Yields 1 serving.

title: church fair peanut brittle
directions: Grease two cookie sheets.
Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan and cook to 280° on candy thermometer.
Add the salted nuts and cook to 300°.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 teaspoons soda.
Pour immediately on the prepared sheets and spread them.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and oil; stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add eggs and flour.
Knead on a floured board.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until it doubles in size and may at this time put in refrigerator or make into rolls.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: quick peanut butter candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until a soft ball forms when dropped into cool water.
Add vanilla.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Pour onto a buttered pie plate.
Cut, when nearly cold, in small squares.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Put ingredients in 3-quart pan with lid; cook, covered, on top of stove until meat is tender and at desired consistency (usually 3 to 4 hours).
Boil, then simmer.

title: eggless eggnog
directions: In pitcher, whisk together first three ingredients.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg before serving.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Blend margarine, flour and chicken broth over medium heat.
Add sour cream and blend until thoroughly warm.
Do not boil.

title: jiffy soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soup, water, lemon juice, garlic, onion powder and pepper.
Mix well.
Add frozen peas; stir to blend.
Let mixture come to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add ham, olives and eggs, stirring until heated through.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *Eight ounce block of cheese and 1/2 cup milk may be substituted for cheese spread and water.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add rice and seasoning and cook until rice is clear.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and bring to a boil.
Lower flame.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.
Add nuts.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into one 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: strips of sauteed chicken
directions: Bone chicken
and
cut	into
strips; lightly dust with flour. Saute on each side until golden brown in olive oil and butter. Add
lemon	juice.	Simmer	until soft.
Serve on hot platter and garnish with parsley.

title: semi-sweet dipping chocolate
directions: Combine milk powder, cocoa and wax in food processor or blender; blend to soft powder.
Pour into top of double boiler and add water, stirring to blend.
Add liquid shortening.
Place over hot (not boiling) water and cook and stir until wax pieces are completely dissolved and mixture is thick, smooth and creamy. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar replacement and let cool slightly.
Dip candies according to recipe.
Shake off excess chocolate.
Place on very lightly greased waxed paper and allow to cool completely.
(If candies do not remove easily, slightly warm the waxed paper over electric burner or with clothes iron.)
Store in a cool place.
Yield: 1 cup (250 ml).

title: poached pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in skillet with water.
Add seasoning salt and pepper; cook over moderate heat until water is mostly gone.
Add small can sauerkraut and cook for couple of minutes longer.
Serve everything together.
Very good.

title: chocolate, oatmeal and peanut butter candy
directions: In a medium size saucepan, bring to boil the sugar, butter, cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Bring to boil 1 minute, then add 1/2 cup crunchy peanut butter and stir in.
Then stir in oatmeal and cook 1 minute.
Pour into pan and let cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths; cut onion into eighths.
Coarsely chip the green onions.
Add along with the garlic to the margarine in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion to margarine; saute for 1 minute.
Add potatoes and pour in broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Puree soup in food processor or blender in batches that will suit the size of the appliance you are using. Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg to soup.
Chill if served cold, reheat to serving temperature if served hot.
Garnish servings of soup as desired.
Serves 4 (or for 8 use only 1 1/4 cups whipping cream).
Garnish with crisp croutons (if served hot). Cold:
Chopped chives, green onion tops or parsley.
You can make this soup ahead and refrigerate it.

title: cinnamon-honey butter
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add honey and cinnamon, beating until well blended.
Yields 1 cup.

title: sweet potato and carrot tzimmes *
directions: In a large pot, bring water to a boil.
Add the sweet potatoes and carrots and simmer, uncovered, until tender (about 15 minutes).
Drain and mash.
Add salt.
Place in greased 6-quart casserole with the prunes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine orange juice, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over the sweet potatoes. Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Uncover and taste.
If the tzimmes taste sweet enough, dot with butter and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.
Or if more sweetness is desired, add pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges; dot with butter and bake additional 15 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: mama's muffins
directions: Mix together, then cook 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Cook zucchini and onion until tender.
Mix together soup, milk, rice and cheese.
Drain zucchini and onion; mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May be topped with crushed crackers and butter, if desired.

title: pralines
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
After it comes to a boil, test for soft ball stage by dropping small amounts in a cup of cold water.
When the drop can be rolled without breaking, remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until shine is gone and it is semi-stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper that has been coated with margarine, and allow to cool.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover. Bring to a boil in the same water, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour. Drain; save water. Put half of pork in 6-cup bean pot. Add beans, molasses, onion, mustard and 1/2 cup bean water. Put other pork half on top. Cover and bake in a slow oven (300°) for 5 hours, adding bean water if needed. Uncover. Bake for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and juice.
Add walnuts.
Chill until firm.

title: super easy sweet potato pone(servings:  6)
directions: Grate sweet potato in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients except marshmallows.
Bake in buttered 8-inch square casserole 1 hour at 375°.
Remove from oven; place marshmallows on top of casserole and return to oven until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour dressing over the mixture.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: pineapple chutney
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice. Combine juice, sugar, vinegar, garlic and salt in a saucepan; stir well. Cook uncovered over medium heat for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add tidbits, almonds and remaining ingredients, stirring well. Cook until green pepper is tender. Serve with lamb or curried chicken. Makes 2 cups.

title: lovenda's dream salad
directions: Combine pineapple, Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: wagon wheel chili
directions: Cook pasta and set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine chili, tomato sauce, ketchup and chili powder.
Mix well; heat through. Drain and rinse pasta; stir into chili.
Garnish with cheese if desired.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: crowd pleaser casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in slightly salted water.
Cook to crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.
Shake container often.
Serve drained, but save liquid to store leftovers.
Will keep for at least 1 week in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour,
sugar
and	soda.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail. Beat well.	Bake
in 300° oven for 45 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain, add butter and mash.
Mix together sugar, egg, mayonnaise, pepper, onion, salt and cheese; add to squash.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white bean and tuna salad
directions: Combine beans, tuna, tomato and onion in large bowl.
Combine lemon juice and mustard in small bowl.
Gradually whisk in oil. Add to salad.
Mix in chopped basil.
Season with salt and pepper. Line plates with lettuce leaves.
Spoon salad on lettuce. Garnish with whole basil and serve.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Drain and set aside.
Cut bread into cubes and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle sausage and cheese over bread.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese.
Chill for 8 hours. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes; do not overcook.
Try adding mushrooms, onion, green pepper, etc.

title: fat-free confetti dip
directions: Scramble eggs over low heat.
Beat in cream cheese, vinegar, sugar and Tabasco sauce.
Add chopped vegetables to your liking.

title: quick cheese calzone(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine cheeses, mixing well.
Using a sharp knife, cut halfway around edge of pita.
Open to form pocket.
Spread cheese mixture inside pita.
Wrap in foil and bake about 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 1 serving.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and egg yolk together. In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices. Gradually stir in milk and cream. Stir in pumpkin. Pour filling into pie shell. Bake for 10 minutes at 425°F (220°C). Reduce heat to 350°F (175°C) and bake for an additional 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, onions, rice, salt and pepper together.
Make into small round balls.
Brown in skillet, drain well.
Pour soup and water over cooked meat balls.
Stir and cook until sauce is thick.
Serve warm.
Serves 3.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water. Stir well. Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans. Put 1/2 in refrigerator. Let jell, then add sour cream on top and pour rest of Jell-O over this.

title: california cocoa
directions: In 1-quart glass measuring cup, combine cocoa and sugar.
Add about 1/2 cup of milk to make smooth paste, then stir in remaining milk, orange rind and almond extract; blend thoroughly.
Microwave on High (10) for 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour into mugs and add cinnamon sticks for flavor or stirring.

title: clam chowder(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Chip bacon.
Add onions; fry until brown.
Put strained clams and potatoes in; cover with just enough water to cook.
When done and some water has evaporated, add clam liquid, milk and seasonings.
Make a paste of melted butter and flour to thicken chowder to desired consistency.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Drizzle each cluster with about 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate.
Chill 5 to 10 minutes or until chocolate is set.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: rice casserole
directions: Pour raw rice into casserole; add soup.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion to soup.
Pour melted mixture over rice and margarine. Recipe can be halved.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, salt and milk together.
Beat eggs, sugar and add margarine last.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chili beans and macaroni
