directions: Cook the macaroni according to the directions on box. Brown beef and onion. Drain off grease and add the stewed tomatoes. Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste. Add beans and macaroni. Cook on medium heat, stirring often. Cook until it is thoroughly heated. Serve with saltines and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in pan.
Mix in graham cracker crumbs. Melt 2 sticks of butter in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Spread over crumbs and butter mix in pan.
Cut bananas and place on top of mixture.
Add one layer of pineapple (crushed) over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Over Cool Whip, add nuts and cherries.

title: chili
directions: Sear meat, onion and flour.
Place in cooker.
Add chili blend, chili powder and garlic salt and blend well.
Add tomato juice and water and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low and cook about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs and soda.
Mix well. Add mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done in center.
Let cool.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven
to
Clean
bell
pepper.
Heat
1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt
to
a
boil; add peppers and cool for 5 minutes;
then
drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; stuff peppers with mixture.
Stand upright in ungreased baking dish. Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover, bake for 15 minutes.

title: 3-layer pudding cake
directions: Crust: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts. Mix well. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs; stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Cut raw bacon into 1/2-inch pieces and roll in spices.
Cut many slits in eye of round.
Push coated bacon pieces into slits. Brown roast in olive oil and margarine.
Remove meat and brown the celery and onion.
Pour wine, broth and tomatoes into roasting pan.
Set beef into mixture which should come 1/3 to 1/2 way up on the roast.
Cover pan and place on middle rack of oven preheated to 350° for 2 or 3 hours, until meat is done.
I have used a 325° oven.
Slice to serve.
Serve strained sauce in gravy boat. Serves 10.

title: mother's oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 12 cup muffin tin with margarine.
Combine oat bran, brown sugar, walnuts, raisins, baking powder and salt.
Add skim milk, eggs, honey and oil.
Mix until ingredients are just moistened.
Fill muffin tin and bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Per muffin:
160 cal., 6 sat. fat.
Without walnuts:
144 cal., 5 sat. fat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add creamed mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour.
On a well floured table, roll out dough about 1/2 inch.
Bake 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: israeli thick lentil soup
directions: It is not necessary to presoak lentils before using them. Simply combine all ingredients, except lemon juice and poultry meat.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and chicken.

title: plantation fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Blend dry ingredients together; add to milk mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: surprise burgers
directions: Form beef into 8 thin patties.
Season.
Lay cheese on four patties.
Cover with remaining patties and pinch edges together. Brown on one side; turn over and pour sauce over burgers.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: garden chicken pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Cook chicken, pepper and onions in oil over medium-high heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Add undrained tomatoes and tomato sauce. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Add hot pasta to skillet. Toss and sprinkle with cheese and heat until cheese is melted. Serves 4.

title: zucchini and tomato with herbs
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in zucchini, bay leaf, basil, oregano, pepper and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes.
Stir in chopped tomatoes and sugar. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Yields 5 servings (1 cup servings), 36% from fat.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Roll out pie crust together to fit a large cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan with pineapple and juice and cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple and cherries.
Cut up butter over top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over cake.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange peaches in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over peaches. Bake until topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fisherman's wharf jambalaya
directions: Brown Rice-A-Roni in butter.
Add hot water.
Stir in flavor pack.
Add celery, bell pepper, onions and Spam.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 more minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well.
Add flour and salt, 1 cup at a time.
Pour batter in a greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: indy slush
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and boiling water; cool.
Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in containers the size that you can use all at one time.
Take out of freezer far enough ahead (4 hours for a gallon) to be a slush.
Goes equally well at a picnic or a formal dinner party.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Mix in chocolate, then flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts. Drop by teaspoons 1 inch apart.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: dreamy chicken stew
directions: Combine soup, 1 cup of water, celery, onion and seasonings in a large pan.
Add
chicken;
cook
over low heat 1 1/2 hours. Stir often.
Add
vegetables
with	1/2
cup of water. Cook 45 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Work in flour
until dough is stiff enough to roll good. Makes 15 pies.

title: fish casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for 1/2 cup of mayonnaise.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover top with remaining mayonnaise. Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cheesy sour cream potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package instructions. Chunk butter and stir in until melted. Add salt to taste.

title: funny-face fruit sandwiches
directions: Combine cottage cheese and cream cheese in a blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
Stir in fruit and nuts, if using. Open pitas and spread one-quarter of filling in each.
Decorate with grapes, bananas and apples.

title: italian pasta sauce #1
directions: *Or, one 14 ounce can of crushed tomatoes and 1/2 can of tomato paste with equal amounts of water.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy cooker.
Cook on medium heat until desired thickness.
Seal in hot sterilized pint jars or refrigerate.
Yields 6 pints.

title: cherry angel food cream cheese dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in milk, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of angel food cake pieces of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 of filling and 1/2 of cherries.
Repeat, ending with cherries on top. Refrigerate.
Makes 9 servings.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: The night before, mix hash browns and margarine.
Pat into crust of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients reserving half and half until last.
Add enough half and half to desired consistency.
Pour into baked crust, refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Kinds of cheese may be varied.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared crust and put in freezer.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, water and vanilla.
Mix well until smooth.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and add cheese mixture and nuts.
Put in glass baking dish or pan and cool in refrigerator.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion in deep container.
Add other ingredients.
Cover; cook on low heat for about 1 hour, stirring often.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots for 15 or 20 minutes in water and seasoning. Saute onions in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, sour cream and milk, blend well.
Stir in carrots.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Cream together graham cracker crumbs, butter and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: quick chicken
directions: Mix together the 2 cans soup and soup mix.
Add water slowly. Pour 1/2 of mixture over the rice in greased baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces over top.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: stuffing
directions: Lay bread out in single layer on table overnight; turn once. In large skillet over medium heat in melted margarine, cook celery and onions until tender (about 15 minutes).
Add parsley, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper to skillet.
Mix well.
Tear bread up and put in large container.
Beat eggs and pour over bread.
Pour skillet mixture over bread.
Mix well.
Add enough milk to make sloppy.

title: crab mousse
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Combine celery and mayonnaise.
Combine water and gelatine.
Combine all ingredients and pour into Tupperware mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Can be served warm in fondue pot.

title: no bake cookies(like candy)
directions: Melt butter, add butterscotch chips and stir until melted over low heat.
Beat egg well.
Add sugar, marshmallows and nuts to egg.
Add egg mixture to butter mixture, stir well.
Place mixture on crushed graham crackers and work and roll to form a long log-like roll.
(It's easier to form 2.) Chill and slice.

title: marinated beef (sirloin)
directions: Put the sliced beef in a deep container.
Add soy sauce, ground pepper and lemon juice.
Marinate for an hour.
Turn the beef once in a while and let it soak.
In a frying pan, put oil. Wait until the oil is hot and then fry the beef (medium fine) for 3 minutes.
Turn and cook for 2 minutes.
After the beef is cooked, take it out of the pan and put it aside.
In the remaining oil, put the onions and the rest of the marinade.
Stir for 2 minutes and add the beef to it.
Cover the pan and turn off the fire.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix together in large bowl all dry ingredients.
Add liquid and stir.
Dough will be very stiff.
Leave in mixing bowl.
Cover and let rise for an hour or until doubled in size.
Heat cooking oil to 370°.
Pinch off walnut size pieces, flattening and pulling hands until each piece is 1/4-inch thick.
Fry until golden brown.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Chill. Serve with apples.

title: fresh green salad
directions: Prepare all vegetables into salad pieces.
Place in large vegetable bowl.
Pour Italian dressing over vegetables 1 hour before serving.

title: meat dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack firmly into loaf.
Bake at 350°, covered 60 to 65 minutes.

title: pumpkin souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put mixture in souffle dish.
Set souffle dish in a pan of hot water.
Place in 350° preheated oven.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until knife inserted in middle of mixture comes out clean.
Chill before serving.

title: mimi's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs and milk and beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Mix together. Shape into mound. Wrap in waxed paper. Chill overnight.

title: cheesy chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Dry chicken with paper towel.
Melt margarine; brush over chicken until completely coated.
Mix remaining ingredients; coat chicken with this mixture.
Place in pan in 1 layer.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes; turn chicken in 15 minutes to brown evenly.

title: duke's souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a deep casserole.
Make layers of cheeses and chiles.
Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff. Beat egg yolks and then fold them into the egg whites.
Gently pour eggs over cheeses and chiles, covering them and ooze through with a fork.
Bake 30 minutes.
Add drained tomatoes, pushing them down with a fork.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: quick delicious salad
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate for an hour and serve.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first; blend in liquids.
Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "squirrel food" or butterscotch walnut squares
directions: Mix like pie crust the first 6 ingredients.
Put down in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Press into this the walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with mixture as follows:

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast,
heaping teaspoonful sugar and 1 cup warm water; set aside.
Cream Crisco, 1/4 cup sugar, egg (beaten), salt and 1 cup warm water.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour; let rise
in
warm place
for
1 hour.
Mash down and refrigerate overnight.	Pinch off
and
pat
with
flour.
Place	in well greased pan.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: reese cups
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar until the consistency to form balls the size of large marbles.
Add vanilla. Mix thoroughly, best done with your hands.
Form into balls. Melt chocolate and paraffin in small double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate, using a toothpick to dip with; place on wax paper to cool.
This candy will freeze well.
Yields 125 pieces of candy.

title: cheddar chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in greased baking dish.
Top with 2 cups finely crushed Cheese Nips.
Pour on 4 tablespoons melted butter. Bake 45 minutes or until done in 350° oven.
Very good!!!
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream everything except flour and nuts, then add them.
Make a ball of dough and put in refrigerator overnight.
Pinch off small pieces and roll into balls.
Pat down on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, until a light brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, flour and nuts.

Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown. When cool, take a fork and crush crust until crumbly; set aside. Combine strawberries, egg whites, sugar and lemon juice and beat 20 minutes at high speed.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla. Pour over crumb mixture and place in freezer until serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil the chicken until it is tender (retain broth). Cut chicken into bite size pieces and spread evenly in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Drain Veg-All and spread over chicken.
In a small saucepan, combine cream of chicken soup and 1 1/2 cans chicken broth.
Heat until smooth and pour over Veg-All.
In a separate bowl, combine Bisquick, milk and butter.
Mix well and pour over chicken and vegetables.
The contents will be runny. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: holly leaves
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat; add vanilla and food coloring. Add corn flakes last and stir to coat. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Arrange 3 red hots on each to resemble "berries."

title: corn flake candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it boils and sugar has melted. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop onto wax paper with teaspoon.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Blend salt, pepper, paprika and sugar in saucepan.
Add onion, tomato, fat and water.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut up chicken; arrange in shallow baking pan.
Brush with hot barbecue sauce.
Cover and bake in moderate oven until about half done.
Uncover; continue cooking and baste frequently with hot sauce until chicken is tender and browned.
Total cooking time is 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate bubble ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease inside of ovenproof ring mold; set aside.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Separate and flatten each biscuit into a 3-inch circle.
Place a chocolate kiss in center of biscuit.
Wrap biscuit around chocolate and pinch edges to seal.
Repeat with remaining chocolate kisses and biscuits.

title: corny quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 450° for 7 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°. Remove pie shell.
Crumble hash into shell.
Top with shredded cheese.
Combine eggs, flour, milk, salt and nutmeg; pour this mixture over hash and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until set.
Cool 15 minutes and serve.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Bake chicken until done.
Cook broccoli.
Place chicken on bottom of casserole dish, add broccoli.
Pour soup and lemon juice on top of chicken and broccoli.
Cover with cheese (layer), then cover with stuffing mix.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350°, until mixture starts to bubble.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In bowl, add soup and water.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
In another bowl, mix flour, buttermilk and margarine.
Mix and put on top of soup/chicken mixture.
Pour chicken broth over flour mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: make ahead french bread (toast)
directions: Butter a large baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, cream, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place bread in baking dish in single layer with sides touching.
Pour entire mixture over bread, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, walnuts and corn syrup.
Spread evenly over bread.
Bake 40 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili casserole
directions: Start with layer of corn chips.
Pour in chili with onions. Cover with corn chips and cheese.
If you like, pour 1/2 can beer over whole thing.
You may use tomato juice.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place 2 cups sugar in skillet or pan and melt it over low heat, before adding other ingredients slowly.
Cook until thick, then put into 2 baked pie crusts. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients; then knead until soft and smooth.
Separate into equal portions and add food coloring to achieve desired color.
Things made by children will dry in air.
To save for later playtime, place in plastic bags in fridge.

title: rhubarb-raspberry jell
directions: Put sugar on rhubarb and let stand overnight in refrigerator. In the morning, cook until done.
Remove from stove and stir in Jell-O.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 2 (18 ounce) jars. Refrigerate.
Delicious.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Put 1 package of cookie dough on bottom of pan.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of cookie dough. Slice the other package of cookie dough and place on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch casserole and pour in mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Also, bacon, ham or hot dogs can be added to make this a main dish.

title: favorite rice pudding
directions: Use 4-quart heavy cook pot.
Put all ingredients in pot except eggs.
Cook on medium-high until nice and thick, about 1 hour. Stir often so rice does not stick.
After thick, remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Be fast with the eggs when you stir them into the rice pudding.
Use a wire whisk to blend together and sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Serves 10.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add tomato sauce and next 4 spices; let simmer 5 minutes.
Slice zucchini and layer noodles and zucchini.
Cover with mixture of cottage cheese, egg and flour, then layer of ground beef. Repeat layers until all used.
Cook in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: super ice cream recipe
directions: Mix all together and finish out with regular milk up to "Fill" line on freezer.
Add different type fruit to add variety.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onions, green pepper and garlic.
Heat oil in pan.
Add chopped ingredients and saute until tender.
Pour off oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato soup, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, oregano, bay leaves, red pepper and salt and bring to a boil. Cook 1/2 to 1 hour on low heat.
Brown ground beef or sausage and add to sauce.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in small bowl; beat until fluffy. Stack 3 slices of bread; trim off crust.
Cut into squares.
Spread mixture generously between slices.
Spread on top and sides thinly. Continue with rest of the bread.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: danish meat loaf(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, soaked bread crumbs, eggs, onion and flour together with the hand.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture appears light and frothy.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Form a loaf of the mixture in a baking dish.
Put the bacon on top and bake for about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste several times during baking with the juice or stock.
Slice thinly when cool.

title: snack crackers
directions: Place crackers in large bowl. Sprinkle dressing mix and dill over crackers; gently toss to coat. Drizzle oil over crackers; toss again.
Place in large Ziploc bag for a day. Serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meat; drain, then add onion and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and set aside 1/4 cup of mixture. Mix and congeal remaining mixture with strawberries and pineapple in oblong dish or mold.

title: nutty-wheat pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, wheat germ, sugar, baking soda and salt. Stir in buttermilk, egg, oil and vanilla.
Drop 1/4 cup batter onto hot skillet.
Make 4-inch pancake.
Makes 4 servings.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cheese and sugar.
Mix in pineapple, strawberries, bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Put in 9 X 13 glass pan and freeze several hours.
Serve frozen.

title: ham and noodles casserole
directions: Arrange alternate layers of ham, noodles and sour cream in a casserole and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven 15 minutes until hot.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer in dish in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: supreme green beans
directions: Cook beans with dill weed.
Drain.
Add mustard and cheese; mix lightly.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese so it is easily mixed.
Add brown sugar and mix well. Serve with sectioned apples or other fruit.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water, salt and lemon juice.
Add cold water last.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate until it only begins to gel.
Then add pineapple and bananas.
Chill until set.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Grease and flour 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until done; let cool.
Combine pudding mix with milk; beat cream cheese into pudding mix and fold whip topping by hand into pudding mix.
Spread on cooled cake.
Put pineapple on top of pudding mix and sprinkle with cherries, nuts and coconut.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: bob's homemade salsa
directions: Clean peppers - remove stems and white membranes (not all seeds).
Chunk onions.
Put garlic cloves & onions in food processor, (large size) coarsely chop.
Add seasonings.
Chunk all peppers and add to food processor.
Process peppers into coarsely chopped pieces.
Chunk tomatoes and tomatillos and add to food processor.
Process tomatoes and tomatillo and parsley.
Add tomato sauce and vinegar.
Process all in food processor until mixed.
DO NOT OVER PROCESS.
LEAVE COARSE.
Makes 4 7 oz. jars.
Bon Appetit!

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes (I steam mine).
When tender drain; set aside.
Melt margarine in small skillet.
Add sugar and honey and blend together.
Add carrots and cook 3-4 minutes over low heat, stirring so each carrot is glazed.
Sprinkle with fresh mint or parsley if desired.
Will make 4-6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, water and rice. Add chicken. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Bake 1 hour at 400° covered with foil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In casserole, put rice and chicken, skin side up.
Beat together the soup, water (milk) and seasonings and pour over chicken/rice.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° until done and brown, approximately another 30 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex container.
Melt margarine and combine with the graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in bottom of pan. Spread chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool thoroughly and cut in squares.

title: robert's hamburger dish
directions: Brown meat, onions and bell peppers and salt and pepper. Drain off fat. Add rotel tomatoes and tomato sauce and chili powder. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Stir in macaroni. Simmer for 15 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: christmas salad
directions: Add water and sugar to cranberries and simmer 10 minutes.
Add can of pineapple, nuts, jello and apple.
Pour into mold or Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: burger bundles
directions: Season 2 pounds ground beef and form into patties.
Make an indentation in each pattie and fill with Stove Top stuffing. Place in roaster.
Mix together any cream soup (chicken, mushroom or celery), ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over top of the patties.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt in bowl.
Stir cornmeal into mixture.
Combine eggs, butter and buttermilk.
Stir liquid ingredients into cornmeal mixture with fork.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in large bowl.
Mix water, oil, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and flour to the mixture and stir well.
Then add buttermilk, eggs, soda and salt.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauteed cabbage
directions: In a skillet or wok, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add cabbage; cook and stir until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat; add soy sauce, sugar and pepper. Cook and stir for 3 to 5 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Serves 6.

title: new kind of corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased iron frying pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut in triangles and serve hot.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Add all canned ingredients to meat.
Grate cheese.
Layer in a large dish: chips, meat sauce and cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: rocky road candy(this is a microwave recipe.)
directions: In a 4-quart microwave-proof mixing bowl, combine chocolate, butterscotch and butter.
Cook on 70 (Roast) for 5 minutes or until melted.
Stir.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set (about 2 hours). Cut into squares.
Makes 45 servings.

title: white bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk, 1 cup water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup water and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat for 1 minute.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic with bubbles under the surface (10 to 12 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down, cover and let rise again until doubled.
Shape into two loaves and place in greased loaf pans.
Grease top of loaves lightly.
Cover.
Let rise.
Bake 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Set 1/4 Bleu cheese to the side and blend remaining ingredients in a blender. Add remaining Bleu cheese. Add garlic salt and pepper to taste, optional.

title: deviled pork cutlets
directions: Brush pork cutlets with mustard on both sides.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large, preferably nonstick skillet, until hot, but not smoking.
Fry cutlets in 2 batches, 2 minutes per side, until golden brown, adding more oil as needed.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 with 295 calories per serving.
Exchanges:
1/2 starch/bread; 3 lean meat; 1 1/2 fat.

title: imperial chicken casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine celery, onions, chicken, cheese, eggs, nuts and noodles.

title: corn bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix with electric mixer.
Add the liquid and mix until smooth.
Place in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheese and bacon party grills
directions: Mix all together.
You can stuff mushrooms or celery or spread on crackers or bread.
Put under broiler for 5 minutes, until bubbly.

title: skillet chops 'n rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Drain fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chops from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Add water and celery.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in rice. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Place large skillet with 5 tablespoons of bacon drippings in oven.
When skillet and drippings are very hot, pour drippings in cornmeal mixture.
Stir and pour back into skillet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni & cheese(macaroni & cheese for 50)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water with 5 1/2 Tbsp salt.
Drain and rinse.
Add macaroni to slightly beaten eggs, grated cheese and remaining salt and pepper.
Place in 10 x 20 inch pan.
Bake 350° for 1/2 hours or until firm.
Cut into two inch squares.
Serve at once.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Dissolve gelatin in juices from fruits with water added to make 2 cups.
Add fruits and nuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.
After set, sprinkle with coconut.

title: tuna salad
directions: In medium bowl, stir sandwich spread, tuna and relish.
Add eggs and onions and toss until blended.
Makes 3 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a small mixer bowl, thoroughly mix all dry ingredients (except raisins).
Combine buttermilk and margarine in a saucepan and heat on low until liquid is very warm (margarine does not need to melt).
Gradually add liquid to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1/4 cup flour; beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in raisins and enough additional flour to make a soft dough. Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead 20 times, forming a smooth, round ball.
Place on greased baking sheet; press dough to flatten into an 8-inch circle.
Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Sprinkle dough lightly with flour, then cut a shallow cross in top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.

title: zucchini and tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and thinly slice zucchini.
Peel and thinly slice tomatoes and onions; divide onion into rings.
In a deep sided 3-quart casserole, place a layer of zucchini, tomatoes and onion rings.
Sprinkle a bit of salt, pepper, brown sugar and basil over the onions.
Add a liberal handful of crumbs, a few bits of butter and a handful of cheese.
Repeat twice, the top layer should be cheese.
Bake, covered, for a total of 1 1/4 hours.
Remove lid after 1/2 hour and continue baking for another 45 minutes or until the center is bubbling hot.

title: parsley pesto
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and then mix into hot pasta.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer 1:
Melt butter in large square baking dish.
Add graham cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Pat down smooth in pan.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Place bread, sausage and cheese (stir).
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over top of meat, bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Use 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well; roll out and cut.
Bake at about 350° until lightly browned.

title: cheesy california vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Microwave, covered, 16 to 18 minutes, stirring at least twice. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Mix all ingredients together and dot top of salad with whole maraschino cherries.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Combine butter, yogurt and thyme or basil.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, leaving 1/4 inch potato next to the skin.
(Use rest of potato for mashed potato.)
Brush inside of the potato skins with yogurt mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until crunchy and brown.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 5 minutes, then add the jello.
Put into jars and seal.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boil. Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale; chill until partially set.
Blend fruits; fold into gelatin.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: white sauce for creamed chipped beef
directions: Melt butter on low.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, and boil for 1 minute.
Add 1 package of torn up dried beef.
Stir well.
Serve over mashed potatoes or toast.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.

title: dirt cake
directions: In small bowl, mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
In large bowl, beat pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add cream cheese mixture and beat together.
In flower pot, put layer of cookie crumbs, alternate with pudding mixture.
End with cookie mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add artificial flowers before serving.

title: quiche
directions: Cook bacon; mix all ingredients.
Pour in each pie crust. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, granulated sugar and shortening. Add the eggs, water and soda.
Mix together.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix together and form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mrs. orr's old fashion candy
directions: Bring sugar, cream and white syrup to a boil.
Boil until hardened; test in cold water.
When it hardens, put in soda and nuts after removing from stove.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, stirring until cooked through; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix, seasoned salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chiles; blend well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In small bowl, combine ricotta cheese and eggs.
In bottom of 13x9x2 inch baking dish, spread 1/2 of meat mixture.
Top with 1/2 of tortillas; spread 1/2 of ricotta cheese mixture over tortillas and top with 1/2 of grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat layering, ending with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 20-30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares. Serves 8.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a sprayed baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until potatoes are done.

title: angel cookies(yields 5 dozen)
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar beating well.
Sift flour with baking powder and add slowly to egg mixture.
Add vanilla. Drop by
1/2 teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet - 3 inches apart. Bake 5 minutes at 400.

title: native american casserole
directions: Dissolve chicken bouillon in 1 cup water. In a large skillet, brown sausages for 5 minutes. Add chicken breasts and brown 5 minutes. Add all other ingredients, including bouillon, and simmer 5 minutes. Turn off heat and let set 5 minutes.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add the sugar, vanilla extract, chocolate and eggs; mix well.
Place the crust on a baking sheet.
Pour the mixtures into crust.
Bake for 35 minutes or until the filling springs back when touched lightly.
Cool on a wire rack.
Spread the cherry pie filling over the top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Dip chicken in melted oleo and garlic salt.
Roll in potato chips.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: spicy lemon chicken
directions: Place a large saucepot over high heat and add oil.
Add onion and jalapeno pepper and
saute until well browned.
Add salt, pepper and carrots, cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken broth, Dijon mustard and lemon juice and simmer for 5 more minutes
Add chicken into the sauce, let simmer on medium-low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add olives when ready to serve.

title: strawberry sparkle cake
directions: *Note:
You can use different kinds of fruit and then change the kind of gelatin and food coloring. Also sugar-free gelatin can be used to make this a dieter's delight.

title: campfire casserole
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon and drain on paper towel reserving 2 tbsp drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: fruity peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Spread each bread slice with peanut butter.
Top with one slice of pineapple for each sandwich; add slices of bananas. Place remaining slices of bread, peanut butter side down, on fruit.
Cut and serve at once.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Remove crust from bread and spread with cream cheese.
Cut bread slice in 3 strips.
Roll strip around an olive and wrap with 1/3 slice of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350 degrees until bacon is crispy.
These freeze well before baking.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Heat juice and seasoning. Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved. Place in refrigerator to mold.

title: bean and corn dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients well.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until serving time.
The longer it sits the better it will taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix and chill before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat the eggs; add the milk, seasonings, butter and corn. Turn the mixture into a shallow, buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake in a pan of hot water at 350° until it will not adhere to a knife inserted 1-inch from the edge, about 1 hour.

title: hot wings
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add all other ingredients. Fry wing sections. Place in ovenware dish. Pour sauce over wings and heat.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry the corn tortillas individually in a small amount of oil. Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with a layer of the fried tortillas.
Spread some of the beans, meat, cheese and onion on top.
Pour enchilada sauce over it.
Repeat in layers, ending with sauce and olives on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve hot with sour cream.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Mix well, roll into balls.
Mix 6 oz. butterscotch chips and 1 box paraffin together in double boiler.
Dip balls and place on wax paper.

title: humdingers
directions: Melt sugar and oleo; add dates.
Cook over low heat for 6 minutes.
Add pecans, vanilla and Rice Krispies.

title: chili con queso cheese dip
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine; add garlic powder, cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes and peppers.
Over low heat, stir until cheese melts.
For richer texture, let set overnight or until cooled in refrigerator. Serve hot in chafing dish or fondue pot with crackers and corn chips.

title: trace leche cake
directions: Cut the cakes into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces and place on bottom of a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Jean recommends Major Market's pound cakes. Mix the 3 milks together and pour over the cakes.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Top with the Cool Whip and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Top with the fruit.

title: skillet green beans
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in margarine until tender. Add beans, salt and pepper. Cook until heated through. Serve with sour cream; sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 2 packages broccoli according to package directions; cook until moisture is gone or firm.
Pour in milk, eggs, 1/2 cup butter, salt, onion and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: make-ahead asparagus appetizers
directions: Remove crusts from bread and flatten bread slices with rolling pin.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread cheese mixture generously on bread slices.
Place asparagus on edge of bread (cut to fit) and roll bread with asparagus in center.
Cut in thirds.
Dip each appetizer in melted margarine.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
When frozen, store in freezer bags.

title: little angels
directions: You will need medium mixing bowl, large spoon, measuring cups and spoons and cookie sheet.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove skin and bone.
Combine salmon with next 6 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours. Roll into 8 x 2-inch log.
Combine nuts and parsley; roll log to coat.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Core peppers and place in a baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and fill the peppers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf - special
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in ungreased muffin pan. Makes 12 individual little loaves.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fish cakes from leftovers
directions: Stir all ingredients with the mashed potatoes, except cornmeal and butter.
Add some flour if the mixture is too thin to form into cakes.
Dip the cakes into cornmeal and fry in butter until browned on both sides.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until done.
Mix squash and all ingredients except bread crumbs together.
Place in a greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In medium size bowl, chop cranberries with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Stir in apples and orange peel; set aside.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add other ingredients and place mixture into 1 pie shell.
Turn other pie shell upside down on top of other pie.
Cut or poke holes in top crust for ventilation.
Do holes in a pattern if you want something more attractive. Sprinkle a little Sweet 'N Low over the top.
Drizzle melted butter or baste it over top.
Bake at 350° until brown for 25 minutes or so.

title: opera creams
directions: Melt ingredients together slowly, boil 3 or 4 minutes; flavor and put in a cool place.
Pan should not be touched until absolutely cold; then beat until resistant and creamy, drop into round balls on waxed paper.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Mix and pour into 1-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken devine
directions: Butter a casserole dish. Place chicken then broccoli in the dish. Mix other ingredients together and pour over the chicken and broccoli. Cover with 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-pudding cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan according to package directions.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to package directions. With a spatula, spread pudding on top of cake.
Drain pineapple well.
Press into pudding evenly.
Top with Cool Whip, spreading it on also with a spatula.
Top Cool Whip with chopped walnuts. Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch overnight cookies
directions: Mix and form into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Spray or grease 13 x 9 casserole pan.
Line with bread slices, but do not overlap.
Top with chicken.
Pour on melted butter (can omit if desired).
Sprinkle on water chestnuts and dot with mayonnaise.
Place cheese slices on next.
Mix eggs, milk, and dry mustard together and pour over all.
Spoon soup on next.
Cover with foil and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Add buttered bread crumbs the last 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Store in covered container.
Mix 1 part mix to 2 parts hot water.
Makes approximately 60 servings.

title: 10-bean soup
directions: Wash dry beans.
Cover with water.
Add 2 tablespoons salt (optional) and soak overnight.

title: papa bertolone cookies
directions: Mix Crisco well, first with sugar, vanilla and anise.
Then add eggs.
When soft, add flour.
Mix well.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook macaroni according to directions on box; drain.
Mix with meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce and chili mix.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese slices.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hermits(cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Put teaspoon soda in hot water to dissolve.
Sift seasonings with flour; add chopped raisins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet (greased lightly).

title: quick and easy cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream with sugar.
Beat in eggs, salt and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Chill.
Top with fresh peaches, strawberries, etc., or canned fruit pie filling and topping.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in soup until smooth, then add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring now and then.
Serve over toast.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a large bowl or food processor fitted with the metal blade, combine all ingredients until blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve or up to 2 days.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with roll mix and bake according to directions on package.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch dressing and spread over cooled dough.
Top with broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery, onion, mango, etc.

title: hawaiian ice
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and blend well with a spoon. Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.
When frozen, put 3 or 4 cubes in a glass and pour ginger ale over them.
Garnish with cherry, if desired.

title: quick chili con queso dip
directions: In heavy saucepan, place tomatoes, chilies, cheese and hot pepper sauce over medium heat. Heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients (except sauce).
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown meatballs over medium heat.
Transfer to a baking dish and pour barbecue sauce over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all together and put in covered bowl and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Place strips of meat on oven racks and bake for 8 hours at 125° to 150°.
Let cool and store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: oven barbecued turkey legs(4 servings)
directions: Wash and dry turkey.
Blend flour, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Dredge turkey with this mixture.
Heat oil in heavy frying pan; add turkey parts.
Brown evenly on all sides over medium to high heat.
Stir together marmalade, chili sauce, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and celery seed.
Put browned meat into shallow baking dish.
Spoon chili mixture over evenly.
Cover dish. Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until turkey is tender; baste once or twice with sauce that collects in bottom of pan during baking.
Good served with hot fluffy rice, green vegetable and salad.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In saucepan, blend
soups.
Slowly
heat through, stirring often.
Top with
sour
cream, chopped tomato and sliced, pitted ripe olives, if
desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables for dipping.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: lemon cooler(yields about 3 cups)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and frothy, adding more ice cubes if a thicker consistency is desired.
Garnish with thin lemon slices.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix together.
Cook about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, pecans and butter; press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese; spread on cool crust.
Mix 1/2 Cool Whip with chocolate pudding; spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown and set.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs, onion, green peppers and 1 can sauce.
Line a pie pan with this.
Cook rice.
Put on top of meat. Pour 1 can of sauce over this and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Prepare broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Mix well in casserole dish with soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit torte
directions: Whip the cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla until creamy.
May need to add a little milk.
Add powdered sugar and continue whipping for a few minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and cool for 2 hours, then add topping/pie filling.

title: muscadine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first five ingredients together. Beat about 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and 4 tablespoons of additional muscadine juice together and pour over cake.

title: delicate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and beat.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition and beat vigorously.
Bake in a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with mocha frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Shred into small pieces and put in baking dish, a layer of chicken, a layer of stuffing, a layer of soup.
Put stuffing on top to form crust.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: raisin cake
directions: Have raisins completely cold before starting. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease lightly 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter or margarine thoroughly; add eggs, one at a time. Beat until fluffy. Sift flour, salt, soda and spices. Add alternately with raisin juice, beating smooth each time. Stir in cold cooked raisins until well distributed; pour into pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine with sugar. Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla and beat batter well. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Blend it into the cream mixture. Stir in nuts. Drop the batter from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10-15 minutes. Cool and spread with icing.

title: cocoa chiffon cake
directions: Combine boiling water and coca; stir.
Let cool.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix with oil and egg yolks. Add vanilla to cooled cocoa and flour; beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture in thin stream over entire egg whites, gently folding in with rubber spatula until completely blended.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan and bake for 55 minutes at 325°, then turn oven to 350° and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: fresh apple coffee cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cut cookie roll into 12 equal slices. Cut each slice into 4 quarters.
Put 1 quarter in a miniature muffin pan and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
While cookies are hot, put a miniature Reese's cup in center.
Seal edges with spoon, then put 1/2 pecan on top.
Makes 48 tarts.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in baking dish (flat) with remaining ingredients.
Spread 1 cup mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, top with boiled eggs (sliced) and bacon bits.

title: homemade yeast bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: omelette
directions: *For a bigger omelette, use 3 eggs and 3 tablespoons water.

title: rose's birthday cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 inch pan, combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits(serves 6)
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick thoroughly to make dough. Make into bite-size balls and bake on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve piping hot.
Makes about 60 small biscuits.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in dressing.
Remove from dressing and bake at 350° until brown.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pecans and coconut. Spread over bottom of pan.

title: chicken and rice(light and zesty)
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Place rice and vegetables, (onions, if using) around and under chicken.
Combine soup mix and Italian seasoning.
Pour over the chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add stuffing.
Spread one-half of mixture over bottom of casserole dish.
Reserve one-half for the top. Spread chicken over the layer of herb stuffing.
Add soups.
Fill each can with chicken broth.
Mix and spread over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious to serve hot.

title: kentucky bourbon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, salt, vanilla, sugar and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Turn oven down to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat.
Combine meat, green pepper, onion, spices and tomato sauce.
Place cooked noodles on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle cheeses evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes with foil over top.
Cool a little and cut.

title: one pan chocolate cake
directions: Mix
ingredients
until smooth.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Use an 8 x 8-inch baking pan or double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan
and
bake
for
about	the
same amount of time. Toothpick test will be slightly moist.

title: chicken and dumplings - in a hurry
directions: Boil chicken about 1 hour in water to cover with bouillon, onion, celery and parsley.
Remove chicken and drain broth into another pot to remove onion, celery and parsley.
Debone and chop up chicken.
Add chicken to broth and bring to a boil.
Cut tortillas in squares; add to boiling broth and cook for 5 minutes or until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste (especially black pepper).

title: black forest sweet cherry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and a pinch of salt in a heavy saucepan.
Add milk and cook until simmering.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring.
Stir some mixture into eggs and return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Stir 1/2 cup of this mixture into the melted chocolate.
Spread over the bottom of the pie shell.
Cover and chill remaining filling for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll in balls and place on a cookie sheet.
You may cover cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam for easy removal.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar, salt and flour together in a bowl.
Mix water, margarine, shortening and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour this mixture over the dry mixture in bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs, baking soda, buttermilk and vanilla to mixture.
Pour batter into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Drain corn and add salt and pepper. Stir in sauteed onions and bacon drippings and sour cream.
Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbled crisp bacon.
Bake at 350° just until mixture heats thoroughly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Pineapple should be well drained. Mix all ingredients* into the cream cheese.
Shape into a ball and roll it in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Wash and cut vegetables in desired shapes and sizes.
Allow 4 to 8 pieces per person, depending on occasion and type of use (appetizer, salad, relish).

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and syrup to a boil in a 1-quart casserole.
Boil 2 minutes on High in microwave oven.
Remove from oven; stir in soda and vanilla.
Put popped corn in large brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup over popped corn.
Fold down top of bag and place in microwave.
Microwave for a total of 4 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove bag from oven every 45 to 60 seconds.
Shake well and turn bag over.
Spread caramel corn on waxed paper to cool. Store in sealed Tupperware container.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: cherry cheesecakes
directions: Put cupcake liners in cupcake pans (18).
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each liner. Cream together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon juice. Fill liners 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and put 1 tablespoon cherry filling on top when cool. Refrigerate.

title: oriental turkey bake
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix soup, water, soy sauce, green onions, vegetables, turkey and rice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Sprinkle French fried onions over turkey mixture.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Serves 4.

title: grandmother's chili
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; fry until crisp and drain.
Add onion and ground beef; cook until beef is brown.
Add the soup and kidney beans and simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and 1 stick margarine.
Save out 3/4 cup of the crumb mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add to the rest of the mixture the eggs and milk.
You can add sour cream, applesauce or blueberries, if desired.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans; sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until springs back.

title: peach pie filling
directions: Then leave set 15 minutes.
Then bag and freeze.

title: southwest taco piesanta fe, new mexico
directions: Partially bake pie crust for 10 minutes.
Cool and reduce oven to 350°.

title: butter-rolls(dessert)
directions: Make dough for biscuits.
Roll it out about 1/2-inch thick. Spread butter all over top of dough.
Sprinkle cinnamon over butter.
Sprinkle sugar over cinnamon.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter. Beat in sugar gradually. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in banana.
Blend in flour mixture. Fold in nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pretzels
directions: About 3 hours before serving, melt butter in scalded milk; in large bowl, let milk cool to lukewarm.
Sift together 5 cups flour, salt and sugar.
Sprinkle or crumble yeast onto warm water; stir until dissolved.
With electric mixer at medium speed, mix unbeaten egg and dissolved yeast with lukewarm milk.

Next, mix in flour mixture, a little at a time, then beat until well blended. Sprinkle about 1 tablespoon flour over dough, then cover with clean towel and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled. Meanwhile, grease 2 large cookie sheets.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in covered microwavable bowl.
Cook on High in microwave until tender, not mushy, stirring after 4 minutes.

title: easy party favors
directions: Slice bagels in small rounds.
Spread each little slice with cream cheese, and top each with 1/4 maraschino cherry.
Serve on plate surrounded by parsley.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Spread onion over it and sprinkle grated cheese on it.
Mix the sherry wine, cream of celery and chicken soups together and pour over all.
Bake 2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: gala pecan spread
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk; mix well.
Add with beef, green pepper, onion, seasonings and sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate.
Heat and crisp pecans in butter.
Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: ellen's nut bread
directions: Mix in order given:
milk, sugar, flour, baking powder, egg and nutmeats.
Bake
in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: microwave alligator
directions: Season alligator chops with Season-All or lemon pepper.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart dish and microwave on High for 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: elegant fudge(makes 4 pounds.)
directions: Melt sugar, brown sugar, milk and butter; boil 15 minutes. Just before 15 minutes are up, turn heat to warm.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow cream, chocolate bits, butterscotch bits, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
When all melted, pour into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Store in covered container at room temperature.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix the garlic salt and cornstarch, then dip chicken in egg and roll in mixture.
Brown in hot oil.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil while chicken browns.
Place chicken in baking dish, pour sauce over chicken and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Cook beef sausage in skillet until brown.
Cut up onions and put them in skillet.
Cook until tender.
Pour tomatoes into sausage-onion mixture.
Cook rice while other is cooking.
Takes about 15 minutes.
Serve sausage-onion-tomato mixture over rice.

title: tiny fruitcakes
directions: Birthday cakes may be great at the party, but tend to lose their freshness the day after.
Freeze what's left and use it to make a completely different cake!

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of water if mixture seems dry.
Make patties.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter until glossy.
Add sugar.
Cream until fluffy; add eggs and cream until light and fluffy.
Sift flour before measuring then add all dry ingredients and sift together.
Add flour to creamed mixture, about 1/3 at a time alternating with
milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat mixture 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour into a large 10 inch tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cake is delicious without frosting.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Wash and chop greens.
Heat salad dressing and toss in greens. Toss until well coated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snack-oyster crackers
directions: Blend together and heat just until boiling (don't boil).
Pour over bag of oyster crackers.
Mix well.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Keep in sealed tin or jar.
Dissolve in boiling water.

title: creamy apple slices
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs in bottom of 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice in pan.
Add sour cream and 1 can apple slices over crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Add cinnamon and nuts.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: lemon supreme pie
directions: Blend and sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, water and lemon juice on low mixer speed.
Blend in the dry ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and begins to bubble; cook one minute longer.
Stir in butter and lemon rind. Set aside until meringue is prepared.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Sift flour and baking powder together and put aside.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture in 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (ovens are different).

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Bring broccoli to rolling boil.
Drain.
Stew chicken and debone when tender.
Arrange broccoli and chicken in baking dish. Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: coffee tortoni
directions: Add coffee and salt to egg whites and beat until stiff but not dry.
Gradually beat in 4 tablespoons sugar, continuing to beat until stiff and satiny.
Whip cream; add 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and almond extract continuing to whip until stiff.
Fold cream and 1/2 cup almonds into egg mixture.
Spoon into 12 paper cups inserted into muffin tin.
Sprinkle remaining almonds over the top.
Freeze quickly.
When completely frozen, remove from tins and wrap individually in Saran Wrap.
May be kept in freezer indefinitely.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef and onion together until done.
Set aside.
Mix sauce, soups and Milnot until smooth. In 9 x 13-inch pan layer Doritos (broken in half), meat, soup mixture and cheese.
Layer again.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: shredded chicken taco
directions: In skillet, combine chicken and picante; mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Heat taco shells on baking sheet in preheated 375° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Fill each shell with 1/4 cup chicken mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, black olives, taco sauce and sour cream.

title: walnut raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter and syrup together with rotary beater.
Mix in the nuts and raisins by hand.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set and pastry is nicely browned.
Cool.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Remove tips from wings.
Cut wings apart at joint to make 2 pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients, except sesame seed, in a large bowl.
Add wings.
Refrigerate, covered, turning occasionally, for 8 hours or overnight.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside.
Spread each slice of bread with butter.
Cut into cubes.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put bread cubes in bottom.
Put sausage on bread.
Top with cheese. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour on top.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions and drain excess fat. Combine remaining ingredients in large pot and turn on medium heat.
Add chili powder to taste.
Mix in hamburger meat mixture and heat until warm.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan over low heat until well blended.
Divide into 4 and spoon each portion between 2 crescent rolls shaped into rectangles and pinch sides tight.
Bake according to crescent roll directions.

title: quick no-bake pie
directions: Mix
Cool
Whip
and yogurt and pour in pie shell.
Top with favorite fruit, if desired.

title: 1-2-3 pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Blend oil in thoroughly with a fork. Sprinkle water over mixture; mix well.
Press dough firmly into a ball with hands.
If too dry, mix in 1 or 2 tablespoons more oil.

title: low-fat chicken burritos
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator; set aside.
In a large, non-stick skillet, place chopped chicken, taco seasoning mix and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in salsa and black olives.
Heat tortillas according to package directions.
Keep covered until used.
Divide and spoon warmed refried beans into tortilla shell.
Top with chicken mixture, cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Roll up and serve.

title: st. pat's day one-pot dinner
directions: Three hours before serving time, rinse meat well to remove salt brine.
Place in a large stew pot. Cover with water.
Bring to a boil. Cover and let simmer.

title: baked ziti
directions: Prepare your favorite sauce or use 2 jars ready made sauce. In Dutch oven, prepare ziti macaroni as directed; drain and set aside.
In same pan, over medium-high heat, cook ground beef until well browned, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: jello and cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer until smooth.
Cool but don't let it set up.
In a separate bowl, whip heavy cream until fluffy.
Add Jell-O and whip to keep foamy. Place in a 5 x 8-inch dish and refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve or place in dessert dishes.
(Recipe can be made with a small box of regular Jell-O.)

title: new orleans stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet, leaving in large chunks.
Add onion, cook until tender.
Add water, soup, corn, salt and chili powder. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, and green pepper. Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: cream puff pastry
directions: Add shortening and water; stir over high heat until boiling rapidly.
Add flour all at once.
Stir briskly.
Remove from heat and break eggs one at a time.
Should be smooth and glossy.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 20 minutes.
Slit and place into oven (turned off) for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over very low heat.
Beat sugar and eggs together until well mixed.
Add buttermilk and blend well.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together and press evenly in a 9-inch square pan (ungreased).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy (about 3 minutes). Pour over hot crust and bake about 25 minutes longer (until no imprint remains when touched lightly in center).
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam and put cooked noodles on bottom.
Warm juice from pork and sprinkle over noodles.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle generously with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, until good and hot.

title: venison and noodles
directions: Combine flour, pepper and salt.
Set aside 2 tablespoons flour mix.
Coat venison with flour mix; brown in hot oil.
Add bouillon; simmer for 1 hour.
Add diced carrots and onions.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Mix the sour cream, paprika and flour; add to pan.
Heat for 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: oat bran honey muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix egg whites, milk, oil and honey together.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Fill lightly greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip ideas(low fat dip recipe)
directions: Lemon smoothy - lemon non-fat yogurt. Any flavor non-fat low-sugar yogurt.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Cut chicken in serving size pieces. Brown chicken in a little olive oil.
Add Dijon mustard and a little lemon juice to chicken and simmer for about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Blend cocoa and Crisco.
Add the egg and sugar.
Add rest of the dry ingredients alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. When cool, put two together with Fluffy Frosting.

title: crunchy swiss and ham appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes; chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in cornflakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve while hot. Yields 8 dozen.

title: mrs. smith's stew
directions: Dice
onion
into
small pieces.
Completely tear apart ground beef.
In a 3-quart saucepan, stir all the ingredients together, except corn.
Cover with water and cook on moderate to
high
heat until ground beef and onion are done.
At this point,
add
the corn
and continue to cook until the corn is heated,
but do not overcook.
Serve open-face style on 1 or 2 slices of French bread. Add catsup to open faced sandwich, if desired.
Served
with chilled
mixed sweet pickles.
Feeds 4 hungry fellows.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in a tightly sealed jar. Use in place of store bought seasoned salt in all your favorite recipes.

title: plain white cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan in moderate oven at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until done to touch.

title: chicken or flank steak
directions: Make marinade for chicken or flank steak. Add boneless, skinless chicken breast. Marinate 4 hours to overnight in the refrigerator. Remove chicken breast. Roll with bacon and secure with round toothpicks that have been soaked in water.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Arrange mushrooms in the bottom of a 4-quart casserole. Add shrimp.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in top half of double boiler. Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Form into logs.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill and cut into pieces.

title: delish-peach pie
directions: Cook the cornstarch and water until thick.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
When cool, pour over pie shell filled with peaches.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt oleo in oblong cake pan.
Put in nuts and salt.
Stir every 10 to 12 minutes during baking at 300°.
Test for desired amount of salt.
Drain well on paper towels.
Bake at 300°
for 40 to 42 minutes.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Combine last five ingredients and pour over bread.
Cover pan, place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: jewish sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup nuts and set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add in sour cream and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Put half of batter in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with half of nut mixture.
Pour remaining batter over nut mixture and sprinkle remaining nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: all day salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve.
Great for sandwiches or chips or crackers.

title: clam cream dip(makes 2 cups)
directions: If too thin after chilled, add rest of 8 ounce package cream cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: mamaw's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix half of oil with other ingredients. Pour remaining oil in skillet. Pour cornbread mixture into hot skillet. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken until meat falls off the bone.
Then boil the egg noodles in the chicken broth.
Saute the green pepper and onion pieces in butter.
Melt the cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes, then combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef and vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain and set aside. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add beef, onion and garlic. Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.

title: garden relish
directions: Place veggies and marinade in a large pan.
Bring to a boil. Stir and reduce heat.
Cover and cook only 5 minutes; cool. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: microwave peach pie
directions: Arrange peaches in 8 x 8 x 2-inch square dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Microwave uncovered on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 turn.
Microwave until peaches are tender, 4 to 6 minutes longer.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix oleo and sugar; add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: robert's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and butter.
Beat lightly.
Add syrup, vanilla and salt.
Place pecans in uncooked crust.
Add filling. Bake in oven at 350 degrees from 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake
crescent	rolls as package directs, but roll flat on cookie sheet.
Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and dressing.
Spread
on
crescent
rolls.
Top
with	vegetables (chopped) and cut in squares.

title: carrousel salad bowl
directions: Cook Creamettes according to general package directions. Drain; do not chill.
While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion, seasonings and cheese.
Toss well.
Gently mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on salad greens (lettuce).

title: picnickers
directions: Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Allow to cool slightly. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture slowly to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in greased baking sheet, 11 3/4 x 11 3/4-inch, for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas and measure 1 cup of pulp. Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Beat for 1 minute.
Add the nuts and mix well.
Pour in a well-greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: english toffee
directions: Grease a 2 foot long piece of aluminum foil with butter. Place pecan halves in single layer.
Boil sugar, water and butter until light golden brown.
