Quickly pour over pecan halves and sprinkle crumbled chocolate on top.
Spread with spatula.
Chop remaining pecan halves and sprinkle on top.
Cool in refrigerator. Break into small pieces.

title: spicy roast
directions: Rub garlic over roast.
Put bacon on roast.
Mix flour, cumin and pepper in large roasting bag.
Add roast and vegetables along with water.
Cut holes in bag (1/2-inch slits in top).
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes per pound.

title: cheese chicken bake
directions: In 2-quart saucepan in hot margarine, cook onion until tender. Stir in milk and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni and cheese and chicken (save 1/4 cup cheese).
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole pan and bake.
Melt remaining cheese on top.

title: mema's spiced pears
directions: Wash pears; leave stem ends on.
Scrape blossom ends.
Boil pears in just enough water to cover for 10 minutes.
Drain and prick skins with fork.

title: corned beef stew(working man's meal)
directions: Saute chopped onion in hot oil in skillet, do not brown. Break up can of corned beef, add to onions, heat through.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add creamed corn and cook additional 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and hot sauce, if desired.
Serve over mashed potatoes or toast.
Serves 4.

title: easy 7-day refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 c. warm water. Cream shortening and sugar add beaten egg, 2 c. warm water, salt and yeast mixture to the creamed shortening and sugar follow with the flour and mix well. Put in large greased bowl. Mixture should be more than double in bulk. Cover tight and keep refrigerator. When ready to use, remove only that which is needed and knead on floured surface for several minutes. Roll into walnut sized rolls for they will triple in size. Set an inch apart on greased pan; let rise for 3 hours. Bake 400° for 12-15 minutes. Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen medium size. Recipe may be halved.

title: creole tomato and peanut butter soup
directions: Heat oil in a 2-quart pot and saute onions and pepper about 5 minutes until soft.
Add cayenne and cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in flour and when smooth, add milk and peanut butter.
Continue to cook over moderate heat, stirring all the while until the soup is smooth, hot and thickened.
This will take 5 to 10 minutes.
Slowly stir in tomato pulp and tomato juice until warmed through.
Makes 1 quart.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Fill 8-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter and adjust top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add raspberries and applesauce to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into mold or into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make the day before so it is set.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Blend soup and flour; add sour cream, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish after sprinkling the stuffing mix-oleo combination on bottom and sides of dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut filet crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
Cut each slice into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place meat and butter in a 2-quart ovenware casserole.
Cook in microwave 9 to 10 minutes, stirring 3 times. Remove meat from dish.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook in microwave 6 to 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain juice off vegetables and add consomme until you have 1 1/3 cups liquid. Return liquid to dish with vegetables.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, catsup and Kitchen Bouquet.
Cook 3 to 6 minutes.
Add wine, dill and meat.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Cook 30 seconds.

title: strawberry meringue cake
directions: Combine cake mix, orange juice, water, egg yolks and orange peel.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soft peaks, then gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Gently spread over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Slice berries.
Whip cream with 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread 2/3 of whipped cream over bottom layer.
Arrange sliced berries on top.
Add top layer, meringue side up.
Garnish with remaining whipped cream and whole berries.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and melted oleo.
Reserve 1/4 cup of crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
In saucepan mix 1/2 cup sugar and gelatin.
Add the water.
Heat and stir until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
Combine sour cream and yogurt and add to gelatin mixture.
Add vanilla. Chill until partially set.
Whip cream to soft peaks.
Fold into yogurt mixture.
Stir in raspberries.
Turn into crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs.
Chill until set.

title: breakfast chocolate molasses sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bring to a rapid boil.
Watch carefully to prevent boiling over.
Turn to lower heat and cook until slightly thick.
You may use this sauce with pancakes or biscuits.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Place 2/3 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoons over cherry filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When still warm, cover with glaze.

title: "homemade stew"
directions: Put all ingredients in a cast-iron Dutch oven.
Bake at 275° for 4 1/2 to 6 hours.
Serves four.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Beat until cool and put in pan.
You can add walnut meats.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter, beat in sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating as you go.
Fold in flour.
Pour cake mixture into a butter tube pan, a round one that measures 27 inches around.
Bake in a slow oven, 325°, for one hour.
Requires no icing but cake develops a wonderful crust during baking.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Bring to boil soup and 3 cans water; add rice.
Cover and simmer.
Set aside.
Cut pork chops into small pieces.
Salt and pepper.
Dip pork into mixture of water and mustard, then roll in flour and fry in cooking oil in skillet until brown.
Add pork to rice mixture, cooking slowly until done.

title: joline's congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt together shortening and brown sugar in large pan.
Stir in flour, salt, baking powder.
Stir until well blended.
In a medium bowl, mix eggs, chocolate chips and nuts.
Place first mixture (sugar, etc.) in a greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Lay second mixture (nuts, etc.) on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian hot pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers; grind and retain juice.
(In measuring peppers, pack solidly in cup and flood with juice.) Combine sugar, vinegar and peppers in heavy saucepan.
Bring to hard, rolling boil; boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pectin and stir.

title: noodles with cream sauce
directions: Boil noodles.
Cut bacon in little strips or cubes.
Fry bacon. Drain fat.
Add onion cubes.
Fry until light brown.
Add cream. Season with beef bouillon cube.
Add flour.
Serve with a big salad.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except biscuits together (after chicken has been removed from bones).
Put in casserole dish. Cut biscuits in quarters and top casserole. Bake at 300° about 45 minutes or until biscuits brown.

title: english scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk to make a soft dough.
On floured board, roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry delite salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan or in a jello mold pan.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: easy corn light bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let bread sit in oven for 1 hour.
Turn out on aluminum foil.
Slice and serve.
Leftover bread can be sliced, buttered and heated before serving.

title: heavenly hawaiian coconut cake
directions: Drain pineapple, measuring juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Combine butter, brown sugar, pineapple and 1 cup of coconut.
Spread in well-greased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Cut each cherry almost through to make four petals; arrange in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, substituting measured liquid for 1 cup of the water and stirring remaining coconut into the batter.
Pour carefully over coconut-pineapple mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan only 5 minutes. Invert on tray and gently lift off pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pepperoni cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan with foil; grease foil.
Chop green onions and pepperoni.
In a small skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook green onions until tender but not browned.

title: chicken caruso
directions: Season chicken with garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute chicken in olive oil for approximately 2 minutes or until it loses uncooked look.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Rinse jar with wine and add to mixture.
Add herbs.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add celery and mushrooms; continue cooking until celery is tender-crisp (about 15 minutes).
Do not overcook.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: applesauce cake(radford 1949 cookbook, mrs. minor wine thomas)
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Blend well.
Add beaten eggs, applesauce, honey and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix 1/2 cup with raisins and nuts.
Add rest of dry ingredients to the applesauce, then add the floured nuts and raisins.
Turn into waxed paper lined pans and bake at 325° for about 1 hour, until done.

title: applescotch pie
directions: Combine apples, brown sugar, water and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until apples are just tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix flour, salt and sugar and stir into apple mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until syrup thickens, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and butter. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: mel's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into ice cream freezer can.
Add milk to "fill" line.
Crank until thickened.
Cover and let set 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: delicious asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Blend in flour.
Add salt and milk.
Return to heat; cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
In casserole dish, layer asparagus and sliced egg, then sauce. Repeat.
Heat in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Crushed Ritz crackers or Rice Krispies may be put on top of added appeal.)

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Toss bell pepper, pimiento, onions, and shrimp together lightly. In separate bowl mix rice and butter; combine the two mixtures. In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients together; fold into the other ingredients and place in buttered casserole dish. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: angel nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites to peaks, add remaining ingredients, mixing by hand.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain and measure juice from beets.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
To this juice add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and cloves, then bring to a boil.
Pour this hot liquid over beets and let stand 24 hours.
Remove beets and add 6 hard-cooked eggs.
Let stand in juice 8 hours.
If you like eggs a dark red, put 1 teaspoon of red coloring in juice before adding eggs.

title: fajita-style chicken breasts
directions: Spray heavy skillet with Pam.
Heat skillet.
Season both sides of chicken breasts with fajita seasoning.
Brown on both sides.
Add about 1/2 cup of water, cover and turn heat to very low.
Simmer until done, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: old fashion chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken slowly until tender in enough salted water to cover.
Cut butter into flour and eggs.
Mix well and roll as for pastry.
Cut into narrow strips.
Drop into boiling broth with chicken and cook for 10 minutes or until done.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: party-perfect cashew chicken balls
directions: Saut onion and celery with 1 tablespoon butter. In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, onion, celery, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise. Form into 1-inch balls, using a teaspoon. Place on a cookie sheet and chill for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn and okra creole
directions: Saute green pepper and scallions in margarine for 5 minutes. Add corn and okra.
Cook over moderate heat for 10 minutes, stirring.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme, salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry or raspberry frosting
directions: Place
all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.	Beat at high speed until frosting is large in volume and of spreading consistency.

title: wham--cheese casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in oil.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: good brown beef stew
directions: Brown meat thoroughly in 1 or 2 tablespoons fat in a large, heavy kettle.
Add remaining ingredients, except carrots, whole onions and potatoes; simmer 1 hour and 45 minutes, adding water, if necessary.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes and cook 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Thicken liquid.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Mix together refried beans with taco seasoning and spread on a plate with an edge.

title: shoo-fly crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, brown sugar, salt and butter to crumbs using a pastry blender.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs for topping.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Line an oblong cake pan with Twinkies.
Pour vanilla pudding (made according to package directions) over top; add pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and crushed candy.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Put all ingredients, except carrots and potatoes, in Dutch oven.
Boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: angel ice cream loaf
directions: Slice angel food loaf lengthwise.

Place a layer of strawberry ice cream 1-inch thick between the cake slices, sandwich style. Make an icing of whipped cream to which marshmallows, nuts, drained crushed pineapple and drained strawberries have been added.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.
Loaf will slice easily as soon as it has been taken from freezer.

title: cappuccino
directions: Store in airtight container.
Per cup use 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon mix; add boiling water.

title: ann landers' pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat in 1 cup flour, then extracts and little ginger ale. Continue alternating flour and ginger ale. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or tube pan. Bake at 275° for 1 hour 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno poppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Coat a large baking sheet with cooking spray. In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, cheddar cheese and mayonnaise; mix well and set aside. Halve jalapenos lengthwise and remove seeds. (Oil and seeds from the peppers can be irritating - wear gloves or put plastic bags over your hands DO NOT RUB EYES.) Stuff jalapeno halves with cream cheese mixture. Place egg substitute in a shallow dish. Place cereal crumbs in a separate dish. Dip stuffed jalapenos halves into egg substitute and then roll in cereal crumbs to coat. Transfer jalapenos to prepared baking dish and coat with cooking spray. Bake until filling is bubbly, about 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in granulated sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice; set aside.

title: lea's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Next add green pepper, onion and mushrooms together with the ground beef.
In a pot, boil your noodles until you can cut with fork.
After your beef, green pepper, onion and mushrooms are hot, add your sauce.
In a glass dish or a pan, start your layer with your noodles first, your hamburger sauce, then your cheese on the top layer.
Keep on layering like that until you run out of space.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes on 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, drain and chop spinach; do not cook.
Add dry soup mix, mayonnaise, sour cream, water chestnuts and onion.
Combine with spinach and soup mix.
Scoop out center of one loaf and place dip into the hollow.
Cut up second loaf (and center piece) of bread into cubes for dipping.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water. Add well beaten egg, flour and shortening.
Mix well.
Let rise to double its bulk.
Stir down with spoon; cover and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Before baking, shape in rolls and place in two greased pans.
Let rise to double bulk for about 1 hour. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until puffy.

title: christmas holly
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in Dutch oven over low heat.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Sprinkle with a few cinnamon imperials.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Combine other ingredients and put in casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well.

title: easy turkey chowder
directions: Remove meat from turkey carcass; reserve.
Break up carcass and place in a large deep kettle.
Add water, m.s.g., salt, parsley, celery, onions, bay leaf, bouillon cube and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cover zucchini with boiling water, let stand 5 minutes, drain. Fill pie shell with mixture of zucchini and all other ingredients except butter.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl until smooth.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Shred lettuce and put on bottom of serving platter.
Spoon mixture over lettuce and spread to 1 inch from edge.
Top with shredded cheese, tomatoes, olives and sour cream or your favorite taco toppings.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix together and serve with various crackers.
Very yummy.

title: hannah's groovy garlic bread
directions: Put butter in a small pan or microwave bowl.
Crush garlic and add to butter.
Heat butter and garlic on stove or in microwave until melted.
Cut sourdough flute horizontally and brush on butter and garlic mixture.
Heat in toaster oven or broiler until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: maple cream coffee treats
directions: Mix brown sugar, maple syrup, nuts and butter together and pour in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, butter, 10x sugar and coconut together.
Put in the biscuits.
Press the biscuits out and put cream cheese mixture in fold.
Lay, folded side down, in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy lasagna(makes two 8-inch square pans)
directions: Mix cheeses and egg together, then add last 4 ingredients. Layer sauce in bottom of pans, then add noodles in single layer. Add layers of sauce, cheese mix and meat; repeat layers.
End with noodles and sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top. Bake 18 to 20 minutes in microwave with cover or plastic wrap. Bake one, and freeze the other!
Thaw before heating.

title: chocolate waffles(simply delicious!)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk and eggs; beat with wooden spoon just until blended.
Gradually add melted butter, beating until smooth.
Bake in waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions.
Serve warm with pancake syrup or, for dessert, with ice cream, fruit-flavored syrups and sweetened whipped cream or top with chocolate Cool Whip.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package (no salt).
Drain; blend in soup, cheese, eggs and milk; stir in broccoli.
Put it in a baking dish.
Pour melted butter over and toss with crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crumbs are brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: california chicken
directions: Boil vegetables briefly in a small amount of water, about 10 minutes.
Make a cream sauce from margarine, flour, milk and salt. Cook until thick.
Use any leftover vegetable water in place of milk.
Layer vegetables and fish alternately with cream sauce in greased casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas pickle
directions: Bring to a
boil
and let get cold:
sugar and vinegar. Mix cucumbers and salt;
let stand 1 hour.
Drain in colander; don't rinse.
Put
in bowl and add onions, bell pepper, celery seed, mustard
seed
and	pickling
spice.
Mix
all together, cold. Put in
jars;
cap	and store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 pints.

title: yummy yams
directions: Whip above in mixer.
Place in buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Combine corn flakes, pecans, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well and sprinkle topping on yams.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: crabmeat mold
directions: Heat soup; add cream cheese to melt.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to warm soup and cheese mix.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Make evening before.

title: pizza
directions: Put dry yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, 3 tablespoons of oil and 2 cups of flour.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead 5 minutes.

title: barbara's christmas cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, milk, butter and vanilla.
Stir and mix well.
Separate into 2 balls. Roll out 1 ball at a time onto floured board and cut out cookies. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and ice as desired. Yields 10 dozen!!

title: coconut surprise pie(this pie will melt in your mouth.)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Well-grease a pie pan and pour mixture into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When done, your pie will have a crust, cream filling and coconut topping.
This pie will amaze you!

title: fresh apple cake(club member:  terah)
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to first mixture. Fold in apples, vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together very well and place in a 3 x 9-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Make in large bowl.
Layer lettuce and layer of each, thinly sliced onion, mayonnaise, sour cream, bacon bits or crumbled bacon and layer of peas.
Make as many layers as you want or until your bowl is filled.
Top layer should be mayonnaise and sour cream. Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Mix and serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add mashed bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt which have been combined.
Add walnuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: Grease and dust with flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Make smooth paste of cocoa and boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Blend in eggs.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add cocoa paste to batter, blending well.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted comes out clean.
Frost as desired.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients.
Pour over cereal.
Stir and mix well.
(Use a large container.)
To coat, use a very large plastic bag with 3 cups powdered sugar.
Add coated cereal and shake well.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven until knife can be inserted and comes out clean.

title: lemon filling
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Beat eggs with rotary beater, then stir into boiling water.
Add lemon juice and grated lemon rind. Combine well and cook in top of double boiler until thick and smooth. This filling may be used on top of cake or between layers.

title: yellow butter cake
directions: Cream butter, Sugar Twin and vanilla in a small mixer bowl. Add eggs gradually, continuing to beat.
Blend flour, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
Mix milk and vinegar; alternately add with flour mixture to creamed mixture, beating just until blended after each addition.
Put batter into a greased 8-inch square pan; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center springs back when touched.
Serve with cherry sauce.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn well.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill thoroughly.

title: pecan baklava(sugar-free)
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients in covered saucepan until apple is tender.
Remove fruit.
Keep simmering juices until it is reduced to a thin syrup (approximately 5 minutes).
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Place one phyllo sheet in bottom of pan; brush with melted butter.
Repeat with two more sheets.
Spoon on fruit.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Repeat phyllo layers, brushing with butter between each layer.
Score top with diamond shapes.
Do not cut through.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour reserved syrup over baklava, cut and serve.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, flour milk, 2 egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes, until knife inserted into pie comes out clean.
Whip egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff and put on top of pie.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs (1 at a time), soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and flour.
Mix well.
Add plums.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 325° until done.

title: nutty noodle casserole
directions: Fry together meat and onions until no longer pink.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oleo.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Garnish with pecans (optional).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bernie's doritos casserole
directions: Crunch up Doritos.
Melt enough butter to cover the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the crushed Doritos on the bottom of the pan.
Stand whole chips on the edges.
Beat Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and egg.
Put this mixture on top of the chips. Mix hamburger and spaghetti sauce and pour over the chips and cheese.
Garnish with onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Pour the rest of the Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Put in oven to melt cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream and spoon on top of chicken in casserole dish.
Cover with one stack of Ritz crackers, crumbled. Drizzle one stick melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil for 1 1/2 minutes the first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon out on cookie sheet fast before it hardens.

title: mama's fudge
directions: Mix first flour ingredients in sauce pan, stir over heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: chocolate-peanut buddy bars
directions: Beat with electric mixer peanut butter and butter 1 minute, until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread dough in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until edges begin to brown. Immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate chips on top of crust. Let stand 5 minutes, until chips become shiny and soft.
With spatula, spread chips evenly over crust.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: special chicken pot pie
directions: In a Dutch oven or soup kettle, combine the first 6 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add mushrooms and celery; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender. Remove chicken and vegetables. Debone chicken; dice and set aside. Slice vegetables and set aside. Strain broth, reserving 2 cups. (Discard remaining broth or

save for another use.) Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in flour until smooth. Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened and bubbly. Gradually stir in cream and reserved broth; bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, peas and reserved chicken and vegetables.

title: chocolate and peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: crabmeat and mushroom bisque
directions: In medium skillet, heat 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add next 5 ingredients; saute until soft but not brown.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, heat remaining 2 tablespoons butter; remove from heat. Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Stir in salt, pepper, mace and Tabasco.
Add sauteed veggies and half and half.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat and add crabmeat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Just before serving; stir in sherry.

title: chicken cheese noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water in large pot and cook until done. Remove and debone.
Cook egg noodles in chicken broth.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add this to noodles, then add half and half.
Add slices of cheese and stir until melted.
Add chicken, stir soup until hot.
Add salt to taste.
More water can be added to make soup thinner.
Serves 12.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar.
Add egg, water and oil and mix well.
Grease large muffin tins, fill 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes in preheated oven at 425°.

title: chili
directions: Stir and fry beef until lightly browned.
Add onions and celery.
Stir and brown.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour.
May be served on rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut crunch
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together in large skillet over low heat.
Add
oats, peanuts and brown sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring
constantly,
minutes or until golden brown. Spread
on	 ungreased
cookie
sheet;
cool.
Chill. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Butter crust before putting in filling.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients as listed.
Save out some pecans to even out on top of pies.
Cook on bottom shelf of oven at 300°.
Shake to see if done.
If browning too fast, put aluminum foil over top.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press in a 2-quart Pyrex pan.
Add topping.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg, orange juice and rind.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Blend milk in.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package of yellow cake mix (dry) and 1 cup of chopped walnuts.
Drizzle 1 stick of melted margarine over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts lightly over Cool Whip.

title: stuffed chicken breasts(appetizer)
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Place 1 slice of cheese and ham on chicken.
Roll and secure with toothpick.
Dip in egg, then flour. Place in pan.
Mix soup/sherry and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Thaw and drain crabmeat.
Saute mushrooms in butter; drain and mix eggs, sour cream, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, flour, onion powder, salt and Tabasco.
Fold in mushrooms, Jack cheese and crabmeat.
Pour into 10-inch porcelain quiche dish (greased). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: date nut bars
directions: Chop dates and nuts in mixing bowl.
Add egg and sugar.
Melt margarine in baking pan.
Add melted margarine; mix.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla; mix.
Bake in a 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: orange buttermilk molded salad
directions: In large pan bring pineapple and syrup to a boil.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in the buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into mold and chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: aunt jan's biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, shortening, baking soda and salt. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add buttermilk; mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Roll out and cut into biscuits. Place individual biscuits on cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, pack 12 into Ziploc bags. Take out as many as needed for a meal. Allow to rise for 10 minutes. Bake at 400°. Makes 120 biscuits.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Combine with onion rings.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over bean mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: beef stew
directions: Peel and wash vegetables.
Cut meat into small size pieces. Dice all vegetables and place in slow cooker with meat and seasonings.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to a full boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oats.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper; let set until cool.

title: irish stew
directions: In a No. 8 deep cast-iron skillet, place the solid Crisco. Melt over medium flame.
Add ground chuck and cook until done, stirring frequently (about 20 minutes).
Add diced potatoes and onions.
Cover contents with hot water, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Cover skillet and cook over medium flame for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until potatoes are done.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
I double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Roll into balls. Bake on a cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 2-quart casserole.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lucy's superb hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Corn and eggs provide all needed liquid.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil until brown.

title: he-man casserole
directions: Brown steak in hot fat on all sides over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until golden.
Stir in flour and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven until meat is tender.
Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and eat.

title: ora's lemon fluff
directions: Chill can of milk 3 or 4 hours.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Chill until "sets up".
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled can milk and fold into jello mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and top with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: applesauce nut bread(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Sift flour and spices together.
Mix into applesauce mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch pan sprayed with Pam spray.
Bake 1 hour; cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Let cool several hours or overnight for easier slicing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer for 45 minutes.
Will keep well in refrigerator up to 3 months.

title: saint paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, onion and celery and drain real well to remove excess fat.
Boil soup mix, rice and water for 7 minutes. Mix with sausage mix and put in a tightly covered casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice pudding(serves 8)
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes, then add vanilla.
Chill or serve warm with Cool Whip, cherry or strawberry sauce or plain.

title: dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need one 8-inch flower pot or plastic sand pail, plastic flower (poinsettia at Christmas) and plastic shovel.

title: easy ruth cake
directions: Place in 9x13 pan in order and don't mix.
Bake for 30-40 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickle
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, salt and celery seed.
Let set while dissolving 2 cups sugar in vinegar.
Heat just enough to make sugar dissolve.
Mix all together.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Ready to eat in 3 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar and peanut butter, reserving 2 tablespoons of peanut butter for later.
Spread the mixture and press into the bottom of crust.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle uncooked rice on greased baking dish.
Mix soups and water.
Pour 3/4 of soup mixture over rice.
Stir.
Top rice with chicken.
Cut margarine into chunks and place over chicken.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Before serving, brown, uncovered, under broiler, if needed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water 3 minutes and drain.
Combine eggplant, croutons and half of cheese.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine milk, flour, salt, pepper and oregano. Pour over eggplant mixture and dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Simmer squash in salt water for 5 minutes; drain.
Add to onion, carrots, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Melt butter and mix with herb stuffing mix.
Put layer of stuffing mix on bottom of dish.
Add vegetables, then a layer of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish according to directions on package.
When cake is warm out of the oven, use handle of wooden spoon and poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk and caramel topping over cake.
Sprinkle with candy bar then top with cool whip.
You may also crumble another candy bar on top of cool whip and drizzle a little of the caramel sauce over top to decorate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Separate crescent rolls and put in pizza pan.
Press over bottom.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: make your own honey baked ham
directions: Make crosswise slits, 1/2 inch apart, halfway through ham to where knife touches bone.
Place ham in a large zip lock bag. Stir together sugars, orange juice and cloves.
Pour mixture over ham in bag.
Close bag and soak at least 2 days in the refrigerator.
Place ham in roasting pan, lined with enough foil to cover ham.
Wrap tightly with foil.
Bake at 200 degrees until heated through.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender with 8 to 10 ice cubes. Cover; blend on lowest speed.
Makes 2 large glasses.

title: cranberry mallow squares
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine in medium bowl.
Press evenly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan; refrigerate.
